title: tomato salsa
directions: Mix all. Cover and refrigerate.
Use within 1 week. Serve with tacos, enchiladas, burritos and tortilla chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and orange sections.
Add strawberries (drained) and peach pie filling.
Mix well.
Blend in bananas and grapes.
Chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.
Keeps well for several days.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice onions and peel cucumbers.
Place in an airtight bowl. Mix vinegar, oil, water, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour over cucumbers and onions and shake to cover all.
Seal and refrigerate until crisp.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix 1 cup flour with cherries, nuts, glazed fruit and raisins. Set aside.
Mix 2 cups flour, salt, baking powder and sugar. Add oil, pineapple and eggs.
Add the fruit mixture.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 275° in 2 loaf pans.

title: hot dog wrap-ups
directions: Spread butter on bread. Put butter side down on cookie sheet. Top with slice of cheese. Put hot dog diagonally across cheese and fold opposite ends together. Fasten with toothpick. Bake at 375° until bottoms are browned, about 10 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet with pancake turner.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and milk; hard boil for 5 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add nuts, vanilla, chocolate chips, chocolate bars and marshmallow cream; stir.
Put in buttered pans, one square and one 9 x 13-inch.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add oil and carrots.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to the liquid.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sandy's kiflees
directions: Topping:
Can be a variety of minced nuts or your favorite preserves.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Pick over dried beans and discard any ones that look bad, usually none.
Cover beans with water; bring to a boil.
Turn off. Cover and soak for about 2 hours.
Pour off all liquid.
Add 3 quarts of water and ham bone.
Simmer for about 2 hours until beans are almost tender (al dente).
Add other ingredients and simmer 2 more hours or longer, until the vegetables and beans are tender.

title: baked coca-cola ham
directions: Pour can of Coca-Cola over a country ham.
Bake until done. Gives a great flavor.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into well greased baking dish. Bake at 400° until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Slice cabbage.
Cover with water, salted to taste, and steam until tender.
Drain.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool on paper towels dusted with powdered sugar.
When cool, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: kookie brittle bars
directions: Mix all together, except chips and nuts, in 11 x 15-inch pan. Spread chocolate chips and butterscotch chips and pack in batter. Nuts can also be added, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Do not overbake!

title: mary mccrank's fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix juices with sugar in top of double boiler.
When hot, add egg yolks, slightly beaten and blended with cornstarch.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes; stir in butter after removing from stove.
Dressing may be served plain or folded into whipped cream for fruit salad topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put Stove Top stuffing in a large casserole dish.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add 2 cups of chicken broth and stir in seasoning packet from stuffing mix.
Pour over stuffing.
Place layer of chicken on top of stuffing and spread cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Top with cheese slices or grated cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: steak casserole
directions: Cut steak in serving size pieces.
Sprinkle pepper and garlic to taste.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides.
Put steak in casserole dish.
Make thin (light brown) gravy.
Pour over steak. Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1 1/2 cans water.
Add to steak and gravy; stir.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve with rice, rolls, green peas and salad.

title: one-rise cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: a wonderful cleaner
directions: Add to a pail of hot water to wash off walls.
Your walls won't need to be rinsed and will shine.

title: hot beef for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat.
Makes enough hot beef for 35 to 40 sandwiches.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Combine the yeast, sugar and milk in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a dough hook. Beat on low speed for 1 minute. Add the butter, egg and raisins. Mix for 1 minute. Add the salt, cardamom and flour. Beat on low speed until all of the flour is incorporated, about 1 minute. Then, beat at medium speed until the mixture forms a ball, leaves the sides of the bowl, and climbs up the dough hook. Remove the dough from the bowl. Using your hands, form the dough into a smooth ball. Lightly oil a large bowl. Place the dough in the bowl and turn it to oil all sides. Cover with plastic wrap and set-aside in a warm, draft-free place until it doubles in size, about 1 hour. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the dough from the bowl and invert it onto a lightly floured surface. Pat the dough into a rectangle about 3/4-inch thick. Roll up the dough, beginning with the long side and stopping after each full turn to press the edge of the roll firmly into the flat sheet of the dough to seal. Press with your fingertips. Tuck and roll so that any seams disappear into the dough. Cut the dough into 1-inch pieces. Roll each piece of dough into a smooth, round ball. Line a baking sheet with parchment or waxed paper. Place the rolls on the baking sheet, 1/2-inch apart. With a pastry brush, brush the beaten egg evenly over the bread. Cover with plastic wrap and set-aside in a warm, draft-free place until it doubles in size, about 1 hour. Bake until lightly brown, 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from the oven and cool slightly on a rack. In a mixing bowl, combine the powdered sugar and milk. Mix until smooth. Ice each bun with the frosting in the shape of a cross. Serve warm.

title: bisquick breakfast bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Cook and drain sausages.
Mix Bisquick and water until soft.
Press dough in bottom of pan and up 1-inch on the sides.
Arrange sausage (spoke fashion) on top of dough.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausages. Pour eggs over top of cheese with milk, oregano and pepper.
Bake 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: microwave berry crumble
directions: Spread berries in an 8 x 8-inch microwave dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle over berries. Microwave on Full power (High), uncovered, 7 to 10 minutes or until berries are bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Lower Fat/Sugar Free Version:
Use sugar-free pudding.
Use light cream cheese and one 12 ounce can skim milk (evaporated). Omit cloves.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients.
Mix with Italian dressing. Chill.

title: con queso dip
directions: Dice up cream cheese and Monterey Jack cheese.
Put diced cheese and mayonnaise in pot and heat on low until creamy.
Cut tomato in quarters and hollow out.
(Dice up only the shell). Thaw out spinach or broccoli.
Fold your tomato and spinach/broccoli into the cheese mixture.
Serve warm with chips. Also good on potatoes.

title: mozzarella eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into crosswise slices 1/3-inch thick.
Peel and place slices on foil-lined broiler pan.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Broil until golden brown; turn, brush with butter and season.
Broil until golden brown.
Top pieces with Mozzarella cheese and brown until cheese bubbles. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cook chicken in broth. Remove chicken and shred. Cook vegetables and rice in broth until tender.	Add shredded chicken. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over tortilla chips.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: haystack candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips; add noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool and serve.

title: large banana pudding
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a double boiler.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Pour over bananas, layered with vanilla wafers in a casserole dish.
Make meringue from egg whites.
Top and brown.

title: chicken salad oriental
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar & soy sauce in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat.

title: deer bologna
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in wax paper.
Chill 24 hours. Bake 4 to 5 hours at 225°.

title: chocolate frosted bar cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together until light.
Add flour and oats.
Spread into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately upon removing from oven, sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread over top when melted.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts (optional).

title: olivia's iowa chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper. Add remainder of ingredients in a large kettle and simmer for 1 hour.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells; drain and cool.
Saute onion in olive oil until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add thawed spinach and cook until water dissolves.
In a bowl, combine cottage cheese, egg, Feta cheese, dill and some Mozzarella cheese.
Add spinach mixture and mix all together.
Stuff shells.
Pour jar of spaghetti sauce over; cover with Mozzarella.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke chicken salad
directions: Mix all and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: turkey cucumber pita
directions: Spread dressing or mayonnaise onto insides of pita bread halves. Fill with lettuce, turkey, tomatoes, Singles and cucumbers.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix all together, pour into greased pan. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Place breasts between 2 pieces of Saran Wrap and pound very thin.
Cut 8 long strips from 1/4 pound butter.
Put a small amount of chopped parsley and green onion tops onto chicken breast along with the strip of butter.
Fold in sides and roll, pressing ends together.
Roll in flour and dip in egg plus 2 tablespoons milk.
Roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Chill overnight for several hours.
Deep fry 12 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar, water and salt.
After chopping cranberries, celery, pecans and apple, add lemon juice.
Mix together and add Jell-O mixture to this.
Pour into a long casserole dish and congeal.
Yields 10 to 15 servings.

title: crispy, chewy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, oatmeal, Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in iron skillet.
In separate pan, combine soups and tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Place Doritos in baking dish.
Top with ground beef, then top with soup mixture.
Then top with grated cheese.
Put in oven; heat just until warm.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Thaw frozen strawberries and add to slightly thawed sherbet. Add ginger ale slowly.

title: pork roast
directions: Place meat in roasting pan; place apples around meat.
Pour drained sauerkraut over and around meat.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top and sprinkle onions over and around.
Put pats of butter on and around.
Add the 2 bay leaves.
Put the can of onion soup over and around and sprinkle the caraway over all.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until meat is no longer pink. Turn oven off while putting rest of dinner out, then remove from oven.
Remove bay leaf.
Slice and serve.

title: good and easy cookies
directions: Makes a stiff dough.
Make into balls and mash with a fork. Bake until lightly brown at 350°.

title: marble cream cake
directions: Whip sugar, cream and eggs, then add dry ingredients.
For marble effect remove 1/2 cup batter and add 1 tablespoon cocoa, 1 teaspoon sugar and moisten with 1 tablespoon water with 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Swirl through cake.
This makes a nice 9 x 12-inch flat pan cake.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and ice with chocolate icing.

title: cruzan coons
directions: Cream the butter until fluffy.
Sift in the flour and sugar. Stir in the vanilla and ice water and last of all, the chopped pecans.
Make 2 rolls; wrap in buttered foil and freeze for 2 hours.
Slice off thin slices of dough.
Shape in an oval roll, like a cocoon and bake in a slow oven at 250° until lightly browned.
After they cool, roll in confectioners sugar and store in airtight container.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and core apples. Slice and place in steamer. Combine all ingredients and sprinkle over apples. Cook on high for 12-14 minutes in microwave.

title: potato casserole
directions: Layer potatoes in 12 x 9-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with corn flake crumbs.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: watergate
directions: Stir all ingredients together and serve.
Nuts can be sprinkled on top.

title: baked eggplant slices
directions: Place eggplant in colander; sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and top with heavy plate.
Allow to drain for 30 minutes.
Pat dry with a paper towel.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook in salted water until barely tender the carrots.
Drain. Combine sugar, cider and tomato soup. Stir and pour over cooked carrots. Refrigerate overnight. Serve.
Delicious!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Take pork chops and season with salt and pepper; dip lightly in flour.
Place in skillet using shortening or Crisco and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and set aside.
Then layer potatoes in long Pyrex dish; put diced onion next on top of potatoes.
To this layer, add cooked pork chops.
Pour mushroom soup over potatoes and meat, then add milk over all ingredients. Cover with aluminum foil and bake in a 325° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
(If the potatoes are crunchy and not cooked good, cook longer until potatoes are soft.)
Serve with green salad, French bread and iced tea.
Delicious!

title: deviled crabs
directions: Mix together and form into patties.
Roll in bread crumbs. Fry in deep fat.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix together flour, oleo and nuts.
Spread and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Get cool.
Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Let set, then spread over cheese layer.
Spread rest of Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle few nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: party pumpernickel loaf
directions: Slice loaf diagonally almost all the way through, about 1/2 to 1 inch apart.
Turn loaf.
Slice diagonally again (end up with diamond pattern).
Stuff loaf with pieces of Swiss cheese.

title: mama's blueberry bread
directions: Soften butter or oleo; add sugar a little at a time.
Beat until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add flour a little at a time and mix well; add vanilla.
Stir in blueberries; dough will be stiff.
Pat it in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ghost town vegetable pie
directions: Partially bake pie shell for 12 minute at 425°.
Boil broccoli for 4 to 5 minutes in salted water.
Chop fine in food processor (if using defrosted, drained spinach, just chop a little with knife to break up).
Saute fresh mushrooms in butter until just tender, drain.
Mix together broccoli (or spinach), mushrooms, minced onions and all spices.
Line bottom of partially baked pie crust with zucchini slices.
Spread broccoli mixture evenly on top of zucchini.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl; add milk or light cream and grated cheese.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake pie about 35 to 40 minutes in 350° preheated oven.
Cool slightly before cutting.
Enjoy!

title: lemon jello
directions: Add jello and marshmallows to boiling water to melt.
Put in pineapple and bananas and refrigerate until set.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, green pepper or red (and or) pimento and seasonings.
Chill thoroughly.
Mix well with salad dressing and drained pineapple.
Turn into salad bowl on lettuce leaves. Garnish with egg, slices or quarters and add some green or black olives and small pieces of pimiento for color.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a medium bowl. Add eggs, butter and milk; beat until smooth and creamy; set aside.
If using an electric skillet, preheat to 350°.
Preheat lightly oiled griddle or skillet over medium heat until a few drops of water dance on the surface.
For each pancake, pour 1/4 cup batter onto hot griddle and cook on first side until bubbles that form begin to pop and edges look dry.
With a spatula, turn and cook until second side is a rich, golden brown.
Serve at once with butter and syrup.

title: seeded cheese rounds
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature for easier handling.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in greased tube pan at 300° for one hour and 20 minutes.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan. Cover with water (enough water to cover all ingredients). Cook on stove top for approximately 2 hours. For crisp cabbage, put in cabbage about 1 1/2 hours after other ingredients have cooked. Cook on medium heat.

title: malachi's favorite meal
directions: Fix macaroni according to directions.
Add the 2 tablespoons of milk, then add the slice of cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: deviled eggs
directions: *Also try adding honey mustard instead of the mayo and regular mustard this is great.

title: slush punch for large party
directions: Use any flavor or color of gelatin in a 6-quart container. Combine sugar, gelatin and boiling water.
Stir until gelatin and sugar are dissolved. Add pineapple juice. Mix well and pour into plastic containers and freeze for 24 hours.

title: chocolate popcorn crunch
directions: Pop popcorn and salt to taste; set aside.
In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat. Add chocolate chips, marshmallows and water.
Stir constantly over low heat until melted and smooth. Stir in popcorn until it is chocolate coated. Spread out on a cookie sheet to cool.
Serve in bowls.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: mixed bean salad
directions: Combine beans, onions and jalapeno pepper; toss gently.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over beans.
Mix gently until dressing is evenly distributed.
Chill.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until a knife in the center comes out clean at 350°, about 45 minutes.

title: california chicken
directions: Combine all except chicken.
Brush over chicken.
Saute in nonstick skillet until lightly browned and thoroughly cooked.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place in casserole dish in order.
Bake for two hours at 350°. Cover casserole for the second hour.

title: mrs. polk's nutty apple muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May be made ahead and frozen.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut green peppers in half.
Lay stuffed peppers (meat side down) in baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup water and 1 can tomato soup with salt and pepper.
Pour over peppers.
Cover peppers with waxed paper and microwave about 20 minutes.
Baste at least twice.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make brownies following directions on box and cool completely. Prick holes in brownies and pour liqueur over them.
Prepare mousse and crush bars.
Break up brownies and layer ingredients in a trifle bowl.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Pour boiling water over cucumbers.
Let set 4 or 5 hours. Drain.
Pack in jars.
Mix all ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers in jars.
Process in boiling water 5 minutes.

title: luscious strawberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add berries and mix gently.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add pineapple and juice and nuts.
Mix. Pour 1/2 Jell-O mix into lightly oiled 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or fancy mold.
Chill slightly. Fold sour cream into remaining mixture.
Pour carefully into mold and chill until set.
Serve on crisp lettuce.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: DO NOT use low-fat cream cheese or Cool Whip; pie will not set up.

title: boeuf bourguignonne
directions: Combine cooking wine, olive oil, salt, pepper, thyme and bay leaf.
Slice one onion, one carrot, one clove of garlic, and celery.
Ad to wine mixture.
Marinate beef in this mixture for at least two hours and up to 24 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Remove meat and pat it dry.
Strain marinade and reserve.
Heat 2 Tbsp. butter with olive oil in heavy skillet.
Brown meat quickly on all sides.
Remove meat to a two-quart basking dish.
Deglaze skillet with 1/4 cup reserved marinade and add to baking dish.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl and season. Add onion to fat and saute in frying pan.
Add corn and cook about 20 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: ernie's freezer cucumber pickles
directions: Combine sugar, white vinegar, pickling salt and celery seed in a saucepan and bring to a boil until syrupy.
Let cool.
Mix the cucumber, onion and green pepper in a glass or plastic bowl.
Pour the syrup over all.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stir once a day for 5 days. Put into smaller containers and freeze.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Dissolve sugar in the beer and add it to the biscuit mix.
Mix the dough as you would with any biscuits and bake them as you normally would any biscuit mix.
If making from scratch, just add the beer instead of the liquid called for in the recipe.
Be sure to add the amount of sugar as listed.

title: blender pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender for 5 minutes at high speed. Pour into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chili mac
directions: Boil macaroni according to directions; drain and set aside until cool.
Simmer ground beef until brown.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir occasionally.
Add macaroni, water, kidney beans and chili powder.
Cover and let simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove top and spread cheese evenly on top. Replace top until cheese melts and remove from heat.
Can serve 4 to 6 adults.

title: honey zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, measure and mix together dry ingredients; set aside.
Grate zucchini; measure and set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix together slightly beaten eggs, salad oil, honey, vanilla and zucchini.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring only enough to moisten.
Do not beat.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased, lined 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Push batter into corners. Heat oven to 325°.
Bake 1 hour until bread tests done in center. Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Complete cooling on rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook frozen spinach according to directions.
Drain well.
Mix with dry soup mix.
Add sour cream and mix.
Put in casserole dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Heat in moderate oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Drain tomatoes (reserve 1/2 cup liquid).
Cut up tomatoes. In skillet, brown the pork chops (pour off the fat).
Add soup, reserved liquid, onions, mustard and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Add tomatoes and pickles and heat through.
Combine rice and parsley. Serve pork chops over rice.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Gently wash and clean berries.
Set aside a few large berries for garnish.
In blender combine the rest of the strawberries, yogurt and lemon juice.
Blend to make a puree.
Refrigerate until very well chilled.

title: ranch dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add Hidden Valley and a small amount of Good Seasons (to taste).
Blend thoroughly and refrigerate for at least 2 to 3 hours.
Great with chips and vegies!

title: hot baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a big bowl, mix the margarine and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add the eggs, beating until smooth. Add the 7-Up and extract.
Beat until one color.
Bake in pan for 80 minutes.

title: cajun corn bread
directions: Mix all except cheese well.
Pour into pan and layer with cheese, then add other half of batter.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: incredible tamale pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add chiles, tomatoes and seasonings.
Mix well.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown meat, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Add salt, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Add chili powder and pepper.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Add beans; cook 30 more minutes.
Add water, if needed. Serves 8.
Chili can be frozen.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: diet coke chicken
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil over medium heat except chicken, then add chicken and cover tightly for 20 minutes.
Remove cover. Cook for another 20 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Turn chicken occasionally during the last 20 minutes of cooking.

title: letter pretzels
directions: Preheat oven.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add honey and salt.
Add flour; knead.
Roll pieces on wax paper to form letters.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, while beating, then add flour, salt and soda; beat well.
Fold in sour cream.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: swiss and bacon appetizers
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in greased baking dish.
Beat baking mix, milk, eggs and red pepper until smooth.
Pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: creole shrimp jambalaya
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Cook shrimp in hot oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Remove shrimp with a slotted spoon; cover and chill.
Add carrot, onion, green pepper, celery and garlic to Dutch oven; cook, stirring constantly, 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, broth, water, rice, salt, chili powder, thyme, red pepper, parsley and sugar.
Bring mixture to boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, or until rice is tender and most liquid is absorbed, stirring frequently.
Stir in shrimp and parsley and simmer 10 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated
Yields 4 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion in a skillet.
In the meantime, cook macaroni in salted water until tender.
Boil peas and corn slightly in butter in separate pans.
Put half of the sausage in a 2-quart casserole dish, then layer peas and tomatoes on top.
Next layer remaining sausage, then corn and macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Spread cheese on top, then put into oven until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini puree
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Saute green pepper and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Puree in blender. Freeze in 1-cup containers.
Add to chicken broth or other soups when almost ready.

title: ginger crackies cookies
directions: Sift together flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Form dough into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cookies will crack when done.

title: green chili quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 8 or 9-inch pie pan, pressing pieces together to form crust.
Seal well.
Cover bottom of crust with green chilies.
Place cheese on top of chilies.
Mix eggs, milk and seasoning together and pour over top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until eggs are golden brown.
Serves 6 for lunch or 12 as appetizer.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to boiling; reduce heat and add flour. Stir quickly over low heat until mix forms a ball.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove from tins and let cool.
Split puffs and fill with pudding mixture.

title: super sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Chill at least four hours.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet, or roll into about one-inch balls flattened with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar, colored sugar, sprinkles or cinnamon-sugar.
These cookies keep very well.

title: crock-pot mexican cheese dip
directions: Heat on low temperature in crock-pot for 2 hours.
Makes a mild sauce.
If you desire a hotter dip, use equal number of cheeses. Serve warm with nacho chips.

title: baked apples
directions: Core the apples.
Combine brown sugar, water, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil.
Pour hot syrup around apples. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 60 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serve warm.

title: sweet-and-sour meatballs with yellow rice
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well.
Shape mixture into 24 (1-inch) meatballs.
Place on a rack in a roasting pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.

title: joannie's chocolate-oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix and boil sugar, milk, margarine or butter and chocolate for 2 1/2 minutes. Stir in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and let set.

title: seafood stew
directions: Thaw fillets.
Skin and cut into bite size pieces.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sour cream, then add mix and mix again. Add lemon juice and Blue cheese.
Stir until blended.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with veggies or buffalo wings or thin with milk for salad dressing.

title: chicken breast parmesan
directions: Combine tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and garlic salt in 2-cup measure.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Reduce power to Medium (50% power).
Microwave for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Set sauce aside.
Mix corn flakes crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Dip chicken breasts in beaten egg, then in crumb mixture.
Place in rectangular dish. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at Medium (70% power) until chicken is tender, 9 to 14 minutes, rearranging over half the cooking time (do not turn over).
Pour sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave at Medium (70% power) until cheese melts and sauce is hot, about 2 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamed onions
directions: Peel and boil onions in salted water; drain.
In saucepan melt butter. Add flour; stir.
Add milk; stir until thick over medium heat.
Pour sauce over onions.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.
Delicious!!!

title: dad glenn's famous homemade potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except evaporated milk and chives, in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.
Stir in evaporated milk during last hour.
Serve topped with chives.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar.
Then add milk and flour.
Then add pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: company casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt. Stir in remaining ingredients, reserving 1/3 of the can of onions to sprinkle over top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: president reagan's macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Stir in butter, salt, egg and cheese.
Pour milk just even with top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until set around edges, but a little shaky in center so it will not be dry.
Thickens as it cools.

title: pork and deer sausage
directions: Grind meat one time.
Mix all ingredients in very well. Wrap in freezer wrap
and
freeze.
To
prepare,
slice, while partially frozen, into 1/2-inch thick patties.
Fry until well done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and meat.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased hot skillet.
Spread 1/2 cup cheese over mixture. Sprinkle remainder of cheese over meat.
Add remaining batter. Bake at 350° at least 45 minutes.

title: "spam and green bean casserole"
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut Spam into cubes.
Cook beans half the time directed on the package.
Make Cream Sauce, stirring in Worcestershire sauce.
Stir beans and Spam into Cream Sauce.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate until cold.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking pan; cover with foil. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; stir and bake another 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned cream pie(old recipe)
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Add cream; combine well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with bits of butter. When pie is baking, stir with a fork several times to prevent settling.
Bake at 350° until filling is set and brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Meanwhile, melt butter in large Dutch oven.
Saute green pepper and onion until crisp and tender.
Stir in chicken, mushrooms, pimento, soup, milk, garlic powder and salt.
Drain spaghetti and add to mixture, tossing spaghetti to mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry onions and green pepper in fat until onions become yellow.
Add meat and fry until mixture falls apart. Stir in rest of ingredients and pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour, removing cover for the last 15 minutes.

title: french vanilla pudding with milk chocolate topping
directions: Mix pudding up according to package directions.
Whip in Cool Whip.
Lay graham crackers in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with pudding mixture and repeat layers until you have about 4 layers.
Add 1 teaspoon milk to milk chocolate icing.
Mix well and spread over the top of the pudding.

title: mom's quick bean soup
directions: If using uncooked ham, boil ham chunks in water.
If too salty, pour off water and add 2 fresh cups boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Do not drain beans.
Cook until thickens to desired consistency.
If using leftover ham, combine all ingredients and follow preceding directions.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 2 to 3 quart pan.
Add brown sugar and half and half or whipping cream.
Quickly bring to full boil.
Boil, stirring for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Let cook at room temperature to lukewarm.
Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix gelatin in the cold water, then add 1 cup boiling water. Put in the freezer until it starts to get thick.
Beat all of this together 2 packages Dream Whip using directions on package.
Add lemon juice, pineapple and sugar.

title: homemade butter
directions: Put both creams into a jar with a tight-fitting lid; shake vigorously.
After a lump of butter forms (about 15 minutes), pour off the remaining liquid (whey).
Place the butter on a plate and press it gently with a spoon to remove the remaining liquid.
If desired, sprinkle with salt.

title: cheese wrapped olives
directions: Dry olives.
Combine all ingredients in food processor and work around each olive.
Freeze for at least 3 hours before baking to prevent them from crumbling.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Better if served hot.

title: mini apple dumplings
directions: Separate each biscuit into 2 parts.
Put apples in each biscuit part and pinch together to make dumplings.
Place dumplings in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix together in large container.
You may add nuts and/or miniature marshmallows.
Also, add a drop of red food coloring if the pink is too pale.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Freeze any leftovers (will thaw quickly).
Makes a large quantity.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat eggs together in separate bowl and add a little at a time to sugar and butter mixture until blended. Just before adding milk, put soda into buttermilk and mix well. Alternate milk and flour into butter, sugar, egg mixture. Add vanilla. Bake at 325° in well greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours or until done when a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spinach squares
directions: Combine eggs, milk and butter; add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: rolls
directions: Sift flour, yeast, sugar, dry milk, salt and baking powder together.
Mix in shortening and water.
Let rise 1 hour or until it doubles in size.
Take 2 tablespoons flour and sprinkle over rolls.
Knock down.
Roll out and cut or pinch off.
Store in refrigerator until needed.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, M&M's
and peanuts; set aside.
Melt marshmallows, margarine and oil together. Cool slightly.
Mix with popcorn mixture.
Grease Bundt pan.
Press mixture into pan.
Cool completely and remove from pan.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer.
Cut each muffin half into 6 wedges.
After spreading mixture on muffin, put into freezer on cookie sheet for about 2 hours.
Put in plastic bag and store in freezer.
Bake on cookie sheet as needed (no need to thaw) at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: regal cream cheese cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in almond extract, pineapple, almond and banana.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: marshmallow crispy treats
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add miniature marshmallows and stir until melted and well blended. Remove from heat.
Stir in rice crisp cereal until well coated. Press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jackie's eggplant salad
directions: Cook eggplant in oven at 350° until skin is crackling.
Take out pulp and throw away skin.
Mash pulp in a bowl until soft. Add garlic, salt and pepper to taste, onion, lemon juice and green pepper.
Add tomato chunks, if desired.
Heap in a bowl surrounded by pumpernickel bread and crackers.
Great at parties instead of usual dip.
Serves approximately 6.

title: sausage and noodles
directions: Brown sausage on one side of large frypan.
Add onion and celery on other side in oil.
Add tomato juice. Bring to a boil and add asparagus.
Cook 5 minutes.
Then add noodles.
Cover and simmer on low until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: abbie's salad or dessert
directions: Heat pineapple to the boiling point.
Remove from heat; add jello.
Refrigerate until partly jelled.
Soften cream cheese; add diced cherries and chopped nuts, then fold in whipped cream and add to pineapple and jello mixture.
Pour into mold or square glass dish, 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch.
Let set in refrigerator. Cut in squares or spoon onto dish.
Good with ham dinners or as a cool summer dessert.

title: apple butter
directions: Boil cider until it is reduced to 1 quart.
Add apples and cook slowly until mixture starts to thicken.
Stir frequently. Add sugar, syrup and spices.
Cook until mixture, when cooled on a dish, is of good consistency to spread.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and dip mix.
Add cheese and shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts to cover; chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot creole sausage
directions: Chop and saute onion and celery in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and chili powder; simmer 15 minutes.
Mix cornstarch in water; stir in sauce until thick.
Add hot smoked sausage.
Add chopped green pepper and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and butter bread. Place in a greased oblong dish. Brown sausage and drain. Sprinkle over bread. Place cheese on top of sausage. Mix eggs, half and half, and salt. Pour over cheese. Chill over night. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before cooking. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: fudge squares
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Add margarine, stir until smooth.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs and sugar.
Add chocolate and margarine.
Stir in chopped and floured nuts and vanilla.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean. Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix instant pudding according to directions and pour into pie crust. You can add coconut to the pudding if desired. Smooth Cool Whip over pudding and top with toasted coconut.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, 400° for 15 minutes.

title: blackberry pie filling
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Toss in blackberries, coating well.
Add rum extract.
Pour into no-fail pie crust and cover with top crust.
Crimp edges and cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Remove foil and continue to bake for 20 to 30 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: cheese broccoli bake
directions: Combine broccoli and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, except reserved cheese; mix well.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake,
uncovered, in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil. Can until ready to use.

title: zesty sausage and beans
directions: Combine smoked sausage, beans and salsa in large skillet. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until hot, stirring occasionally.
Serve sausage mixture over rice and top with sour cream and parsley.
Makes 5 servings.

title: egg salad
directions: Grind eggs fine in food grinder.
Add remaining ingredients to taste and spreading consistency, excluding olives.
Garnish each square or triangle with thin slice of olive.
Makes 35 to 40 squares or triangles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Form ball and roll in seasoned pepper.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Three hours before preparing casserole, slice squash, sprinkle with salt and place in colander to drain.
Coat large flat casserole with oil or vegetable spray.
Dip zucchini slices in flour and layer in casserole with cheese and spices.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water, syrup and salt together for 6 minutes or until soft ball stage.
While this is cooking, beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks.
Pour half the mixture into egg whites and beat again.
Put the pan with the other half of the mixture back on stove and boil for another 3 minutes or until it spins a thread.
Boil this while you are beating the first mixture.
Pour into egg whites and add the vanilla.
Beat and pour into buttered platter. Cut into pieces before cooled.

title: chocolate! chocolate! chocolate!
directions: Mix the chocolate pudding with whole milk and half and half. Pour in Oreo pie crust.
Cover with chocolate whip cream.
Shave or grate one chocolate candy bar on top of chocolate whip cream.
The candy bar can be your choice.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat shortening until creamy, 2 minutes, at medium speed on mixer.
Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until thick and pale color.
Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with bananas.
Beat thoroughly after each addition.
Grease the bottom only of a 4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: cabbage roll
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges.
Place in casserole and tuck in small amount of beef around cabbage wedges.
Add the rice; pour over all the mixture of tomatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: In medium saucepan, cook potatoes in 1-inch of boiling salted water, covered, just until tender; drain.

title: venison mincemeat
directions: Fully cook meat. Store in refrigerator in its juice overnight.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.
Serve cold.

title: cucumbers and sour cream
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers.
Add salt to water.
Add cucumbers to salty water and soak about 1 hour.

title: rio grande tamale pie
directions: Grease 10-inch deep dish pie plate.
Brown meat; drain slightly.
Add onion and cumin.
Cook until tender.
Stir in salsa.
Combine cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Set aside. Combine milk, egg and oil; stir into dry ingredients.
Pour cornmeal mixture into pie plate.
Gently spoon meat into center of cornmeal mixture.
Sprinkle with olives.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until crust is light golden brown.
Top with cheese and continue baking until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate eclair torte
directions: Bring water and butter to boil over low heat.
Add flour until it forms a ball.
Cool 10 minutes at room temperature.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 425°.
When cool, press and fill with 2 packages instant pudding, 2 1/2 cups milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix well and stir in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread on crust and chill.
Later, put chocolate frosting over the pudding.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as on package.
Drain.
Add margarine and American cheese.
Cover with Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add oil, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix and pour into a 12 x 18-inch pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Make extra copies of this recipe for everyone who gets a piece!

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: cornmeal crepes with chicken
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, eggs, 1/2 of chives and chili powder.
Heat skillet on medium-high. Brush with oil.
Add 1/3 cup batter and spread out.
Cook each side.
Continue process until batter is gone.

title: captain's favorite(reese's chunks)
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips and pack in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Wait 15 minutes and cut into chunks.

title: strawberry supreme cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cake mix and jello (do not mix up jello, add dry).
Add oil and water.
Beat, then add juice from strawberries. May add a few strawberries, if desired.
Beat well.
Bake at 350°.
Cool.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine onions, cheese, bread crumbs, paprika, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in mixture of egg and milk.
Roll chicken in dry mixture and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: mama's coconut pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick, then pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 275°.
Then beat egg whites and top with meringue. Sprinkle coconut on meringue, then brown.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Line round Pyrex dish with vanilla wafers.
Separate egg yolks, set aside egg whites.
Mix egg yolks, milk and lemon juice.
Pour over vanilla wafers.
Top with meringue.
Brown top in 325° oven. Cool and place in refrigerator.

title: sugar-free rice pudding
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients at medium heat until just boiling. Pour into bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap for creamy pudding.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour, then mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/nutmeg mixture.
Makes 10 servings, approximately 103 calories each.

title: butter fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Bake at 325° for about 8 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Put soft drink mix into blender; add water and strawberries. Cover and blend until smooth. Pour into glasses and serve immediately. Try it, you'll like it.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients in another bowl and pour into the casserole dish.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm, approximately l hour.
Serves 10 - 12.

title: quick chickpea and ditalini meal
directions: Chop celery, pepper and onion; saute in oil with spices.
Add water and cook 20 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce and 1 cup of water.
Stir in chickpeas and cook 10 more minutes.
Cook and drain ditalini.
Add to mixture and serve.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix as listed.
Oil hands and knead slightly.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and put into refrigerator until double in bulk.
Punch down and pinch off; roll into rolls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise in a warm place.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: bourbon dip
directions: Combine ingredients and heat for 25 minutes in saucepan.
The links may be heated, separated and then added to sauce if you want.
Serve with toothpicks, Cheddar cheese and crackers.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Add cinnamon, cloves and pumpkin.
May use 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans, greased and floured, for bars or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan for a cake.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Keeps well in refrigerator or freezer.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook in large
heavy
skillet
over
medium heat sugar, corn syrup and peanuts
until it starts turning brown and will spin a thread, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add soda, salt, butter
and vanilla.
Pour	out
thin
as
possible
on lightly greased baking
sheet.
When
completely cooled, break into pieces.

title: hot dip
directions: Mix all.
Bake in glass pie dish for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: popcorn-gumdrop cake
directions: Combine butter and marshmallows in Dutch oven; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted.
Add popcorn, peanuts and gumdrops, stirring until blended.
Press mixture into well buttered 10-inch tube pan until top is level all around.
Chill until firm.
Invert cake onto serving plate. Garnish with gumdrop flowers, if desired.
Use an electric knife to slice as thin slices cannot be made easily with a knife.

title: lemon crisps
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add lemon and flour.
Roll dough into small balls.
Smash with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: tomato surprise
directions: Pour tomatoes into saucepan, saving can to use as mold.
Bring tomatoes to a boil.
Add jello and salt, stirring until dissolved. Add vinegar.
Pour into can and chill in refrigerator until firm. Puncture bottom of can to unmold.

title: english toffee
directions: Butter cookie sheet and sprinkle on chopped nuts.
Place 5 Hershey bars on pan.
Melt margarine and butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, Karo syrup, vinegar and water.
Stir and boil to 290°.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and boil 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly. Pour hot candy on pan (on top of chocolate bars) then put 5 remaining bars on top of hot candy.
When candy bars are soft, spread with a knife to smooth out.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Cool and cut.
Store in airtight container.

title: steak salad
directions: On 4 plates, make beds of lettuce and salad ingredients of your choice.
Add a layer of cooked French fries and then strips of steak.
Top with your favorite salad dressing.
Serves 4.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt. Gradually stir in boiling water and cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Mix together slightly beaten egg yolks, lemon rind and juice. Add to thickened sugar-water mixture and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add butter. When slightly cool, pour into baked shell. Cover with meringue made by gradually beating powdered sugar into stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: easy french onion soup
directions: Toast bread crumbs in a 325° oven until lightly browned. Brown onions lightly in oil.
Combine boiling water and bouillon cubes in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add onions.
Simmer, covered, until onions are tender, about 15 minutes.
Toss toasted bread crumbs with canola or olive oil and cheese and sprinkle on top of soup just before serving.

title: shrimp with garlic and basil
directions: Heat butter and garlic in heavy skillet.
Add shrimp, parsley, basil, scallions and lemon juice.
Turn shrimp, basting in sauce until they turn white, about 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper and cook 1 minute more.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve on a bed of seasoned rice.
Serves 4.

title: cherries 'n cream roll
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line bottom with waxed paper, grease wax paper.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix together the warm water and dry yeast.
In a large bowl, mix the sugar, salt, oil and eggs.
Mix and add yeast and water. Add flour.
Let raise to double its size.
Divide into 7 equal portions.
Knead and put into greased bread pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: potato dumpling platter
directions: Coarsely slice cabbage.
Discard tough ribs.
Thinly slice onion.
In hot salad oil, cook cabbage, onion, salt and pepper 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender and lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage.

title: herb burgers with rosemary and thyme
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, add beef and blend thoroughly.
Shape into patties.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Cook burgers, searing one side, then the other. Serve with cheese bread.

title: filled sugar cookies with raisins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in small amount of boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain very well.
Add soup, mayonnaise and cheese and mix very well.
Stir in well beaten eggs.
Pour into oiled casserole dish, sprinkle top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Then beat the cream cheese. Add to jello, then pour over oranges, already in pan. Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: taco salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces and put into plate or bowl; cover with chili.
Add other toppings to taste (try them all or just a few).
Top off with the Ranch dressing.

title: chicken king ranch
directions: Saute in butter the pepper and onion.
Soak tortillas in chicken broth.
Line a deep baking dish with the tortillas. Alternate chicken chunks, onion, green pepper and grated cheese. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spread 1 can cream of chicken soup, then 1 can stewed tomatoes. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in water to cover until almost dry.
Mix all other ingredients and pour into raisins.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: double shelled tacos
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning to meat and follow directions on the package.
Submerge tortilla in hot oil for 15 seconds.
Remove and repeat with another tortilla. Layer with slice of Velveeta cheese and reheat in oil while folded over.
Fill with taco meat and top with cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: bing cherry salad cups
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, salt, pineapple and enough food coloring to give a pretty pink color.
Lightly fold in nuts, cherries and banana.
Place cupcake papers in cup cake tins.
When making cupcakes, save the pink cups for this salad.
Spoon salad into cups and freeze.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In 1 cup of water, cook carrot, onion and celery until soft. Add milk and mix flour and water for thickening.
Bring to a boil. Add salt, bacon and broccoli.
Turn off heat; leave on burner and add cheese.

title: fruit surprise pudding
directions: Mix Bisquick, shortening, 2 tablespoons sugar and milk together.
Place berries in casserole.
Drop mix on berries. Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch; sprinkle on top of dough. Pour water over all ingredients.
Serve plain or with milk or whipping cream.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pear preserves
directions: Pare, cut into uniform size pieces.
Cover with sugar and a loose cloth.
Let stand over night.
Begin cooking slowly and boil until tender and fruit has reddish color.
Spoon into hot sterile jars and seal.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Simmer about 30 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars seal.

title: praline cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line the bottom of a jelly roll pan with graham crackers.
Combine brown sugar and butter.
Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Let boil 1 1/2 minutes and remove from heat.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Quickly spoon mixture over graham crackers and spread evenly.
Bake 10 minutes. Set pan of cookies on rack to cool.
Cut or break into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: wassail
directions: Heat all ingredients. Serve warm with cinnamon stick stirrer. Makes 16 (4 ounce) servings.

title: sweet cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together all ingredients until smooth.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Mix white sugar and cornstarch; add brown sugar.
Add milk and butter.
When butter melts, add milk mixture in cup with beaten egg yolks and add to rest of milk mixture.
Stir until thick. Beat and add coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff with 1/4 teaspoon of cream of tartar.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook butter, sugar and milk over medium heat until boiling. Cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Prepare fondue in heavy saucepan.
Add cooking wine and heat but don't boil.
Add shredded cheese slowly, stirring constantly. Dissolve cornstarch in brandy flavoring and add to cheese mixture and stir.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Toast bread in bite size pieces and pour in fondue pot.
Garnish around the sides with bread.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard; set aside.
In large bowl, combine eggs, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 of the tomato sauce mixture and mix.
Place meat mixture in glass ring, mold or 2-quart microwaveproof round casserole.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Cook, uncovered, on High (maximum powder) 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: lakeshore chili(in honor of stallion, "many wishes")
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Peel and chop the onions.
Heat the cooking oil in a large skillet and cook the onion pieces slowly until brown.
Drain liquid from the beans and combine them with the onions.
Tear the corned beef into shreds and place it in the bean and onion mixture.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Stir the mixture well.
Rub the sides and bottom of a baking or casserole dish with softened butter.
Use a ladle to put the chili-mixture into the greased dish.
Bake for 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12 persons.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Prepare cucumber slices, onion and salt.
Store in covered container for 24 hours.
Drain well; add sugar and vinegar.
Let stand in refrigerator another 24 hours.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.
No cooking or canning!

title: treasure island dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
This is a great spread over hamburgers, too.

title: caramel king
directions: Brown 1/4 cup of the 3 cups of sugar.
Mix milk and remaining sugar.
Bring to a slow boil.
Add brown syrup slowly.
Bring to a boil and cook until it forms a hard ball in water.
Beat; add butter and flavoring.

title: hamburger casserole with beans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pita bread
directions: Combine yeast, sugar and water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add mixture to dry ingredients and mix well.
Turn dough onto well-floured surface.
Divide dough in half.
Cover half and set aside.
Divide one portion of dough into 10 equal pieces.
Knead each piece until smooth and elastic.
Shape each into a ball. Cover with a damp towel.
Repeat process with second half of dough.
Let dough rise in warm place 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Place each ball on well floured surface and roll into a 6-inch circle.
Cover with damp towel and let rise 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and pour into buttered casserole dish (13 x 9-inch).
Top with corn flakes mixed with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1/2 cup cold water.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Dough should form a ball.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut into dog bones.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder. Crumble in butter. Set 1/3 of this aside. Add milk, flavoring and eggs to remaining mixture. Spread dough in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pie filling and top with crumbs.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix 2 teaspoons cinnamon with 1/2 cup sugar in Ziploc bag.
Cut biscuits in 4 pieces and drop in cinnamon and sugar.
Coat well.
Layer them in pan with pecans in between.
Melt margarine.
Add 1 cup brown sugar.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then dump.
Use a tube pan to bake in.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips (about 3 strips per 1/2 breast).
Salt and pepper each piece.
Mix together the buttermilk and eggs and place the cut chicken into this mixture.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Then roll each strip in flour and deep fry or pan fry until golden brown.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in heavy 10-inch skillet or square pan (9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch).
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter evenly.
Arrange pineapple on butter-sugar coating.
Decorate with pecan halves and maraschino cherries, if desired.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Stir all dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, milk, egg and flavoring; beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Scrape sides of bowl constantly.
Beat another 2 minutes.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Turn immediately onto serving plate.
Leave pan over cake for a few minutes.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: In a skillet, combine the first six ingredients. Cook uncovered over medium heat for 10 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally. Brush on side of tortillas with butter. Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture over half of unbuttered side of each tortilla. Sprinkle with 1/3 cup cheese. Fold plain side of tortilla.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Mix together milk, sour cream and cream of potato and celery soups.
Add hash browns.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan, covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Put cheese on top and bake uncovered for another 1/2 hour.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1 cup sugar.
Slowly add hot milk.
Let simmer until all of the sugar dissolves.
Mix water, flour and butter.
Add to liquid slowly.
Add egg yolks last.
When mixture is thick, remove from stove and add vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Beat egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Spread on top of pie.

title: american chop suey
directions: Sear meat in heavy skillet in small pat of butter until lightly browned.
Add rice and stir.
Add tomatoes, cut through with knife. Add chopped peppers, onion, celery and garlic.
Stir well, salt and pepper to taste and bring to boil.
Turn heat to lowest flame and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Do not lift lid or stir during last cooking.
Serve over chow mein noodles with soy sauce.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Heat applesauce and red hots until red hots melt.
Add jello and 7-Up.
Place in
9x13 pan and refrigerate until set.

title: country style eggs(cooked in microwave)
directions: Cook bacon 4 minutes at High or until done.
Cook butter, potatoes, onion and green pepper in 8-inch cake dish uncovered 6 minutes at High until tender.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Flatten potato mixture and pour egg mixture over.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes on Medium-high or until egg is almost set.
Stir once.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese over egg.
Heat uncovered 1 minute on Medium-high or until cheese starts to melt. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: flaky sausage snacks
directions: Allow pie crust pouches to stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Unfold pie crusts; peel off top plastic sheets.
Press out fold lines.
Invert and peel off remaining plastic sheets.

title: greenbrier salad
directions: Put water, marshmallows and jello in saucepan.
Heat until marshmallows are dissolved.
Cool thoroughly.
Add pineapple, cheese and whipped cream.
Pour in mold and chill overnight.

title: the ultimate sugar cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 5 to 9 minutes.
Combine sugar and Crisco in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine 3 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix until well blended. Spread 1 tablespoon flour on sheet of wax paper.
Place 1/4 of dough on floured paper.
Flatten dough slightly; turn over and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out with floured cutters.
Transfer to ungreased baking sheets, 2 inches apart.
Cool; frost and decorate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In salad dish, layer ingredients in order listed.

title: fruited cabbage salad
directions: Place oranges, apples, cabbage and grapes in bowl.
Beat whipping cream in a chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold whipped cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt into mayonnaise.
Stir into fruited cabbage mixture.
Serves 6.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Microwave butter on High for 2 minutes.
Add sugar and milk and mix well.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes. Mix well, scraping bowl.
Microwave 5 1/2 minutes; stir after 3 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter, marshmallow cream, peanuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into 8-inch pan.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: peach breakfast pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients. In small bowl, mix the sugar, shortening and vanilla.
After stirring ingredients well, add sugar and shortening to flour mixture and stir.
Grease square cake pan.
Put 1 1/2 cups canned peaches in pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sprinkle flour mixture over peaches and bake for 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon tea
directions: Steep all together 10 minutes.
Add water to make 2 quarts. Sweeten to taste.
Add lemon balm, mint etc., as garnish.

title: low-fat peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour; mix flour, salt and baking soda.
In a separate dish, mix peanut butter, apple juice and vanilla, using an electric mixer.
Blend this with flour mix.
Place by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: tahitian chicken salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, relish and curry powder. Add to chicken mixture and toss gently.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with grape clusters, if desired. Serves 6.

title: meat and dried legume soup
directions: Cook meat and 1/2 teaspoon salt in pressure cooker for 30 minutes with water as required (meat may be cooked on top of stove until tender).
When cooled, cut into bite-sized pieces.
In large kettle, put garbanzo and black beans, 1/2 teaspoon salt and water. Add the water drained off meat.
Cook approximately 30 minutes. Add 1 teaspoon salt with lima, red, kidney and white beans.
Cook for 1 hour more or until almost done.
Add lentils, barley, split peas, onions and spices, adding more water if needed.
Cook until tender.
Add meat and tomato sauce.
Simmer on low burner for 10 minutes until blended.
Add wine, if desired.
Makes 14 pints. Pack into pint containers and freeze for future quick meals.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in a small amount of oil; drain. Add cream of mushroom soup, milk, and green chilies; mix well. Add Doritos and mix together. Pour into a baking dish and lay slices of cheese over top. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: quiche pastry
directions: In small mixing bowl, stir together flour and salt.

With pastry blender, cut in shortening until it has the appearance of cornmeal. Cut in butter until particles form the size of peas. Sprinkle mixture with cold water. Blend lightly with fingers until dough holds together and can be formed into ball.
Roll out to fit a 9-inch quiche dish.
Brush pastry with mixture of egg yolk and Worcestershire sauce.
Microwave on High (10) for 4 to 6 minutes. Makes one 9-inch quiche pastry.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Heat oil and onion. Add water and chicken. Heat to boil. Add salt, cook 3 - 4 minutes. Stir in broccoli, cook 4 minutes. Add milk and cheese. Cook until cheese melts. Put in crock pot on low.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Use in cookie press or form small balls and press with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
You may double recipe.
Store in airtight jar or tin, if there is any left.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a small pan, combine sugar, salt, cocoa and butter.
Boil for 1 minute and then remove from stove.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Using 2 teaspoons, drop on cookie sheet with wax paper.
Chill.

title: chicken puff almondine
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, milk and onion and mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles and seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of roll.
Fold and seal.
Brush tops with melted margarine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle slivered almonds on top last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit platter salad
directions: Arrange different varieties of fruit such as those given on a large divided platter.
Other fruits may be used.
Use seedless grapes and slice apples, pears and nectarines or other similar fruits used.
Serve with Cool Whip or favorite fruit dip.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup and milk.
Stir in noodles, peas, pimento and tuna. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot. Stir.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and halve apples.
In medium bowl, mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Pour in 1/3 cup cold water.
Stir until mixture resembles pie crust dough.
Roll 1/2 cup dough on floured surface until 1/8-inch thick.
Wrap around one apple half, folding dough in an overlapping fashion.
Place seam side down in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Repeat with remaining dough and apple halves.

title: holiday jello
directions: Put in pan and let set.

title: string beans and new potatoes
directions: Remove ends and all strings off beans.
The best way to do it is to hold one end of the bean and pull down the seam and the string will come right off.
Do the other end for the other seam. Bread into 2-inch pieces.
Put bacon drippings or ham hock in pot with beans and add enough water to come about 1-inch above them. Add salt and stir.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours until beans are done.
About 1 hour after beans have been cooking, add potatoes to the pot.
Taste beans for salt.
Refrigerate any leftovers and reheat.
I always cook more than I need for one meal just so I can have leftovers!

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip on large shallow dish with lip on it.
Blend avocados, lemon juice, salt and garlic salt together and spread over beans.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning together and spread over avocado mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese, green pepper, tomato and green onions over mayonnaise mix.
Garnish with sliced black olives.

title: knorr classic spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours.
If desired, serve in a round loaf of pumpernickel bread or as dip for raw vegetables.

title: taco pizza dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with sour cream and taco mix with mixer.
Place in round dish and let cool in refrigerator until set, about 20 minutes.
Dice tomato.
Slice olives.
Place olives on top of dip like pepperoni.
Sprinkle on cheese and diced tomato.
Dip with nachos.
Enjoy.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using electric mixer.
If by hand, beat about 50 beats.
Pour into sheet cake pan greased. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: audrey's pie
directions: Mix ingredients well. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake in preheated oven about 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: pork and noodle skillet
directions: Brown the sliced onion and celery in fat.
Add the noodles and brown with vegetables.
Add pork, bouillon and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spicy vegetarian chili
directions: Heat the oil gently in a large skillet.
Add cumin, chili powder and onion and saute gently until onion becomes translucent. Add bell pepper and saute another 5 to 8 minutes.
Add texturized vegetable protein, if using.
You may add a little water if the pan seems to get dry.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Add tomatoes and salt, cooking for another 15 to 20 minutes.
Add kidney beans and cook until they are heated through.
Taste to adjust seasoning.
Serves 4.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on Ritz crackers and make sandwiches. Melt Hershey bars in a double boiler.
Pour over sandwiches to cover completely.
Let cool and eat.

title: seven layer mexican bean dip
directions: Mash avocado, salt, pepper, and lemon juice together in a small bowl.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Remove casing from sausage and brown in a large skillet, chopping up the meat as you brown it.
Some Italian sausage has very little fat, in which case you might need to use the olive oil. When browned, set aside.
When cool, stir in the egg.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, 3 cups flour and orange juice alternately.
Add flavoring.
Dredge fruit and nuts in other 2 cups of flour, then mix cake batter with fruit and nuts.
Bake at 220° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: joe's shrimp marsala
directions: Remove shells from shrimp and butterfly them.
Dip in beaten eggs.
Dredge in flour and gently shake off excess flour.

title: frozen baci
directions: Place all the ingredients into the jar of a blender and process until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour the mixture into 2 glasses and serve with Baci chocolates or any of your other favorite fancy chocolates.

title: butter dips
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Sift flour and sugar into bowl.
Add milk.
Stir with fork until dough clings.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead.
Roll out, cut in strips.
Dip in margarine.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: light chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 8-inch square baking pan pan with light vegetable cooking spray.

title: moist old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water 10 minutes.
Drain raisins and reserve 1/2 cup of the liquid.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Add raisins and liquid and stir until mixed well.

title: layered congealed jello
directions: First Layer: Make lime Jell-O as directed on package.
Pour in casserole dish and let set until firm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste and add Herbes to the water before you boil the chicken. Put the chicken in the food processor.
Process until very small. Put in bowl and set aside.
Add pecans.
Process the pickles, eggs, celery and then add to the chicken.
Add the grapes and stir well.
Add the salad dressing to make it as moist as you like. Cover the serving dish with lettuce and put the salad in the middle of the bed of lettuce.
Place deviled eggs around the salad, leaving a space between the eggs where the tomatoes will be placed.

title: sausage almond casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain off fat.
Add to sausage the rice, soup, water, celery and mushrooms.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes. Put into greased casserole and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Butter sides of saucepan.
Combine sugar, water, salt, syrup and vinegar in buttered saucepan.
Cook to hard ball stage (290 degrees).
Slowly pour over popped corn.
Stir just to mix well. Butter hands.
Shape into balls.
Makes 15 to 20 balls.

title: lemon delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add honey, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
When mixture gets thick (soupy), fold in whipped cream made with the can of milk.
Line bottom of cake pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Gently spoon mixture over. Sprinkle more graham cracker crumbs over top.
Chill well.
This is a wonderful light dessert for summer.
For a 9 x 13-inch pan, I double recipe.

title: shepherd's casserole
directions: Cook beef until done.
Add onion and cook until onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in green beans, Hunt's Manwich sauce and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Pour into a baking dish.
Spread mashed potatoes over meat mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Place sausage, Bisquick and cheese in a large mixing bowl. Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.
Place on cookie sheet.
Freeze until firm.
Place in plastic bags; freeze.

title: happy meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch and cold water alone and stir into boiling water.
