Cook until clear; let cool.

title: ramen noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package and drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar, dry soup base and olive oil.
Add to cabbage and drained noodles.
Toss gently and chill.
May add nuts, chicken or shrimp.

title: pork chops with caper sauce
directions: Put pork chops in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat. Cover and cook for 5 minutes to draw out some of the juices, then uncover and cook over medium heat until juices evaporate and chops are well browned on all sides.
Set chops aside.

title: crustless spinach quiche
directions: Saute onion in oil in a large skillet until tender.
Add spinach and cook until excess moisture evaporates.
Cool.
Combine eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir into spinach mixture.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Yields 1 (9-inch) quiche, 6 servings.

title: granny's lindberg special
directions: Grind the vegetables.
Mix together well.
Add salt and cover with water.
Let stand three hours.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put into jars.
Process as for pickles.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Put in a butter baking dish, butter side down.
Pour sugar, salt and milk over the bread.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 325° with the dish covered during the first half hour of baking. The top of the pudding should be well browned.
Serve warm with Hard Sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs in 3-quart (13 x 9-inch) glass baking dish; cover with wax paper.
Microwave for 25 minutes on Roast.
Drain; combine remaining ingredients, and brush over ribs.
Re-cover and continue cooking for 30 to 35 minutes on Roast, or until meat is fork-tender (about 170°).
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add hot water, salt and lemon rind and juice.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tuna salad sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Good on any type bread made into sandwiches.

title: capo rep's winter survival soup
directions: First put the chicken in a large pot filled with water.
Boil chicken for 1 hour.
Take the chicken from the broth.
Set aside to cool.
Then put the broth in the freezer so that the fat rises to the surface and you can skim it off.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle cheese and bacon into pastry lined pie pan.
Sprinkle onion on top of cheese and bacon.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until browned and firm.
Cool slightly.

title: best ever hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix chocolate and milk in saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring to blend.
Beat in marshmallow sauce.
(I usually make a double recipe.)

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add salt, cream of tartar and vanilla to egg whites; beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff.
Fold chocolate chips into egg whites.
Cover cookie sheet with brown paper or aluminum foil; drop batter in small teaspoons.
Bake for 25 minutes at 300° or do overnight. Put trays in oven, turn oven off and remove in the morning.
If doing overnight, they must remain in the oven at least 4 hours.

title: coconut cream pie(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake crust for about 10 minutes.
Place on rack and let cool.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan over low heat. Stir frequently until thoroughly combined.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Stiffly beat whipping cream.
Line pie pan with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Fold lemon juice, grated rind and beaten yolks into condensed milk.
Blend well.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Spread stiffly beaten cream over mixture.
Set in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: hot crabmeat spread
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add crabmeat, cheese, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper. Cook over low heat until the cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Serve hot with Keebler Onion Toasts.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and 1 stick butter.
Put into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and most of the powdered sugar together.
(Save a little powdered sugar to sprinkle on top when done.)
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Dissolve in this lemon and orange Jell-O.
Let cool thoroughly.
Add buttermilk, cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a square or long dish. Place in refrigerator to chill well.
Will keep for several days. (Travels well.)

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to boil; simmer for 20 minutes. Bottle; place in water bath for 25 minutes.

title: valeska's banana cake
directions: Cream together the Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add the vanilla and bananas.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add the flour mixture to the creamed mixture with the sour cream or buttermilk.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 40 minutes. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package instructions.
Drain. In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion. Cook until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Blend in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Combine macaroni and cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole. Top with bread crumbs. Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked eggs
directions: Mix eggs, cheese, salt, pepper and oregano together.
Pour into 10-inch buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into slices like a pie.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
This is done to soften the peanut butter which you can help along with the microwave.
Add powdered sugar and blend well.
Fold in the remaining Cool Whip.
Be sure all ingredients are mixed well.

title: caramel brownie pizza
directions: Prepare brownie batter according to package directions.
Coat a 12 inch pizza pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread batter over pan to within inch of the edge.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 - 30 minutes.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Spread caramel apple dip over top; sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add water, if needed.
Stir in shrimp.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour with a spoon.

title: taco pie
directions: Thaw pie crusts; prick bottom and sides of crust and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning mix to meat according to package directions.

title: "roll kuchen" (1)
directions: Knead a little, roll out and cut in rectangle shapes.
Fry in deep HOT oil.

title: christmas wreath punch
directions: Combine orange juice concentrate, corn syrup and lime juice. Mix thoroughly.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice ring. Yield: about 50 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: blueberry drop cookies
directions: Wash and drain blueberries.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening until soft.
Gradually beat in sugar, then egg and grated lemon rind.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth after each addition. Lightly fold in blueberries.
Drop from teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve with raw veggies.

title: tuna mold
directions: Heat soup and stir in softened gelatin. Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise and add to soup mixture. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Oil fish shaped mold or other mold with mayonnaise. Pour in mixture and chill overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: justin's hot chocolate
directions: Take some chocolate and some water.
Put it on the stove and see if it's hot enough.
Take it off and wait 'til it cools off and drink it.

title: coconut pie with self-made crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour (or until knife inserted comes out clean).

title: dottie's cranberry souffle salad
directions: Mix gelatin with sugar and salt; add hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice and rind.
Blend with rotary beater.
Pour into refrigerator tray and quick chill in freezer until firm, about 1-inch from edge, but still soft in center (10 to 15 minutes).
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in cranberry sauce, fruit and nuts.
Pour into molds and chill until firm. Unmold on lettuce.
Top with mayonnaise.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix yellow squash, onions, bell peppers, and Pimentos and cover with salt, add ice, let stand 1 1/2 hours, drain. Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, and mustard seed. Simmer about 5 minutes. Add vegetables, bring to boil. Pack in jars and seal.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Pour milk in top of a double boiler; cut cheese into small chunks.
Add to milk.
Cook over hot water, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Chop pimentos; add to cheese mixture. Stir in salt and paprika.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Store in covered dish in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: broiler-barbecued pork chops
directions: Preheat broiler.
Line broiler pan with aluminum foil. Arrange chops on broiler rack in single layer.
Combine tomato sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, ginger and red pepper in small bowl; stir well.
Spread barbecue sauce over chops.
Broil 6 inches from heat, without turning, until cooked through (10 to 12 minutes). Check after 6 minutes and reverse position of broiler pan, if necessary.
(Do not turn chops over.)
Makes 4 servings each.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water with lemon jello and pineapple juice; allow to set.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Let set.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased (with margarine) baking dish.

title: breakfast diet bar
directions: Mix well. Form into bars. Let set in refrigerator over night.

title: fettuccine carbonara
directions: In a small bowl, beat eggs and mix with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese; set aside.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Meanwhile, cook bacon in a skillet until it is crisp. Pour off half the bacon fat and stir into the pan the cream.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Cook broccoli by recipe on box; drain and set aside.
Saute onions in oleo.
Add soup and 1 can water. Add broccoli, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Mix together, put into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture is bubbly.
Stir gently after mixture has cooked for about 15 minutes and sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and paprika. Serves 8.

title: boeuf abdullah(lebanese meat balls)
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter until transparent.
Cool slightly.
Mix with meat, egg, bread and seasonings.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls; roll in dry bread crumbs.
Brown slowly in remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Gently spoon yogurt over and around meat balls.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with rice or wheat pilaf.

title: cream cheese - crab - potato puff
directions: Boil potatoes and cream with milk until smooth.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add egg, chives or onion tops, crab meat or tuna and salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into Pam-coated casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.
(Especially good as a brunch casserole.)

title: chocolate eclair dessert(children's)
directions: Line bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish with graham crackers.
Combine pudding mix with milk in a bowl.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Spoon layer of pudding mixture over crackers. Add another layer of crackers over pudding.
Repeat layers until all pudding is used.
Cover top with layer of crackers.
Chill in refrigerator until set (usually two hours).
Spread chocolate frosting over top.

title: elephant ears
directions: Sprinkle work surface with sugar.
Place sheet of thawed puff pastry on sugar; sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over puff pastry sheet.
Roll to 14 x 10-inch rectangle; press in as much sugar as possible.
Fold long side of dough to center.
Fold dough crosswise in half to make rectangle.
Fold dough lengthwise in half to make 7 x 2 1/2-inch rectangle.
Wrap in plastic wrap; chill in freezer 15 minutes.
Repeat with remaining puff pastry.

title: chocolate curls
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Pour onto wax paper and spread to 3-inch wide strip.
Let stand until cool but not firm. Pull a vegetable peeler across the chocolate and transfer curls carefully to cake.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, mushrooms, garlic and oregano in oil; stir in flour.
Add beef broth; cook until thick.
Stir in sour cream and spinach.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut cheese into strips, crisscross over hot casserole and bake until cheese melts.
Can be frozen before adding cheese, then bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: tomato cheese rice
directions: Combine stewed tomatoes, butter and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Makes 4 servings.
It is also good without the cheese.

title: chicken-roni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Combine with chicken, cheese, soup, milk, mushroom, pimiento and mustard. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.
This dish freezes well.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Combine 1 cup soft breadcrumbs and 2 tablespoons melted butter. Stir well. Sprinkle over top of casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator and allow to come to room temperature.
Cover and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: baked creole fish
directions: Season fish with salt and pepper.
Distribute onion and parsley over bottom of lightly oiled baking pan (can use Pam spray).
Place fish fillets over onions and parsley.
Pour wine over all.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: veal saltimbocca
directions: Cut veal into 8 equal size medallions.
On cutting board, place 12 inches of plastic wrap.
Place each medallion between layers of plastic; carefully flatten with mallet just before the point of tearing.
Season each medallion with sage, salt and pepper.
Place equal amounts of cheese and ham on the medallions and roll into cylindrical shape, folding sides in 3/4 inch.
Use toothpicks to close.
Roll lightly in flour.
Simmer garlic cloves in butter in large saute pan for 2 to 3 minutes; remove.
Place veal in pan; roll until just lightly browned all around.
Turn up heat.
Add wine just before butter burns.
As sauce forms, turn down heat and stir with wooden spoon until consistent and glossy. Thin with chicken stock, if necessary.

title: valentine's day dessert truffles
directions: Scoop 1/2 cup of the ice cream into a small glass bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until melted.
Reserve 4 large strawberries.
Chop 1/2 of the strawberries and stir into melted ice cream.

title: gramie's dumplings(for country-style chicken and dumplings)
directions: Add baking powder and salt to flour. Cut in shortening. Add egg and enough water to make a dough. Roll out very thin on a lightly floured board. Cut into strips, size as desired, and drop into boiling chicken stock. Let stew until done.

title: reese cup tarts
directions: Cream butters and sugars thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Take rounded teaspoonfuls of dough and place in greased miniature muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookie puffs up and is barely done.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to instructions on package.
Roll out two 9-inch pie crusts.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry. Combine meat, milk, soup mix, pepper and allspice.
Mix gently. Lightly pat into pastry.
Top with potatoes.
Put top crust on pie and seal.
Cut an air hole in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix applesauce and Jell-O on low heat until Jell-O is mixed real good.
(No water, just mix like it is.)
Then put pineapple, nuts and 7-Up.
Mix together really well.
Chill overnight.

title: basic biscuit recipe
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk and stir until mixture leaves sides of bowl.
(Use fork).
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead.
Pat into 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out.
Place on greased sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: shrimp and cashew stir-fry
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Set aside.
In a large frying pan, heat peanut oil; stir in cashews and brown.
Remove cashews with a slotted spoon.
Stir in onion and cabbage in oil, about 3 minutes. Add mushrooms and brown.
Mix in garlic and shrimp, stirring until shrimp is pink.

title: mark's mozzarella marinara
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Cut cheese into twelve 1-ounce pieces.
Dip each piece in egg, then flour, then egg and finally into bread crumbs.
Chill at least 40 minutes.
Fry in 1/2-inch oil until brown on both sides.
Drain well.
Spoon 3 tablespoons marinara sauce on plate.
Top with 2 cheese slices and put a little more sauce on top.
Garnish with Italian parsley.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water in oatmeal; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into mixture.
Add vanilla and oatmeal mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: turkey roll and balsamic sauce
directions: Cut the turkey breast so it is as flat as possible.
Flatten it further with a pounder.
Mix sausage, eggs, Parmesan cheese, onion and juniper berries.
Spread this over the turkey.
Cover with sage leaves and then the Mortadella or thinly sliced ham (not country ham).
Roll the meat and secure the roll tightly with a string. This is a messy job but worth it!
Put the butter and oil in a heavy roasting pan.
Season the breast with salt and pepper.
Cook at 350° for about 60 minutes, adding the wine, a little at a time, to keep the cooking juices moist.

title: wash day peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium saucepan, over medium heat, cook fruit until boiling.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine flour, 1 cup of sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in refrigerator overnight, but not longer than 24 hours.
Grill for approximately 8 minutes per side on medium heat (low rack).
Brush both sides of the meat with extra marinade during cooking.
(This marinade is also good with pork chops.)

title: southwest chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken about 30 minutes; drain.
Chop up.
Combine chicken with mayonnaise, sour cream, green chilies and onions. Cover and refrigerate.
Can be served any way.
Can be served on tortillas.
Place tortillas on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for about 10 minutes until melted.
Top with lettuce and chicken salad.
Garnish with tomatoes and picante sauce.

title: italian baked sausage
directions: In a baking utensil, place sausage, green peppers, onions and potatoes.
Bake at 350° (occasionally stirring the vegetables) until done (approximately 40 minutes).
Enjoy!

title: swiss cheese salad
directions: In a bowl, toss cheese and eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard, horseradish and cumin.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese-egg mixture and toss.
Serve on crisp salad greens.
Serves 6.

title: baked beans for a crowd
directions: Use a 5 qt. baking dish.
Spray bottom and sides of baking dish with cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients except bacon slices in large bowl; pour into prepared dish.
Top with bacon strips, slightly overlapping strips.
Cover dish with foil and bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour or until bacon is brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with cream sauce.
Then sprinkle with extra Parmesan cheese. Bake in 350° oven until warm through.

title: cafe vienna
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Artificial sweetener can be substituted for the sugar and coffee creamer for the powdered milk, if you prefer.
Prepare 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: apple raisin stuffed chicken
directions: In a skillet, saute chicken (cubes or tenders) in the butter until just barely cooked through. In a small mixing bowl, combine the cream of mushroom soup and the half and half.
Place the chicken on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add the soup mixture. Stir to coat the chicken.
Pour the bread crumbs from the stuffing box on top of the chicken.
Cook the seasoning packet from the stuffing as directed on the box and pour on top of the bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baked fudge
directions: Cream eggs and butter.
Sift cocoa and flour together.
Add to eggs and butter.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Set in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
The top will be crusty; inside will be soft.
Serve warm in bowls with a scoop of ice cream.

title: dip for apples
directions: Mix ingredients and serve with apples.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Spread Miracle Whip mixture, then sprinkle cheese over top, then bacon.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.

title: duke's cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar and salt.
Stir in whipping cream and coffee cream.
Mix good.
Line pie pan.
Dice in butter, then pour in cream mixture.
Bake on top shelf at 425° until brown.
Gently stir, after brown, with a fork.
Put on bottom shelf, lower oven to 375°.
It will take 55 minutes or 60 all total according to your own oven.
(Take out when center still shakes.)
It will finish cooking after you take it from oven.

title: apple crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel, core and cut apple into 8 slices.
Cut each crescent in half lengthwise and make 16 long triangles.
Place apple at wide end of crescent dough and roll up. Place in a buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over the top.
Add orange juice and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt in double boiler butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over crispy cereal.
Put powdered sugar in brown grocery bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake until cereal is coated with powdered sugar.
Spread on cookie sheet and refrigerate.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then pour Italian dressing over and mix in.
You want it moist.
Sometimes after it sets it gets dry and you will have to add more dressing.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon flour.
Mix beaten egg and vinegar.
Add juice drained from pineapple. Cook until thick, cool.
Pour over Delicious apples, crushed pineapple, peanuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix well.
Add 2 cups tap water.
Mix well again.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cake is very moist.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cook onion, celery and pepper until tender.
Drain.
Add chicken and other ingredients.
Cook spaghetti and mix with sauce.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: teresa's beer batter for halibut
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use for deep frying fish or veggies.
We use it for halibut that has been cut into bite sized pieces.
It's delicious.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Prepare pie shell by cutting away 1/2 inch and rolling remainder between wax paper.
Save the 1/2 inch in freezer bag. Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients in small mixing bowl. Beat in 2 eggs, vanilla, and butter.
Add rhubarb to batter.
Pour into shell.
Shake a little cinnamon on top.
You may add strips of leftover crust across the top or save the leftover crust in a freezer bag for another time.
Bake at 400° for 45-50 minutes.

title: foil cheese dessert
directions: Blend together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake paper.
Fill cups 3/4 full and bake at 350° to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and spoon pie filling on top.
Can be frozen to use later also.

title: tuna swiss pie
directions: Bake pastry at 375° for 10 minutes; remove.
In large bowl, mix first three ingredients together.
Spoon into pastry.
In bowl, stir together rest of ingredients.
Slowly pour over tuna mixture.
Bake 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole with almonds
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain well.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour; add milk and cook, stirring, until thick. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add salt and pepper and remove from stove.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in airtight container.
Serve in hot, hot water: 1 cup add 2 tablespoons mix. Stir.

title: tater tot feast
directions: Grease 2 qt. baking dish.
Cook onions and ground beef in skillet with salt and pepper.
Spread mixture in baking dish, cover with soup and tater tots.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip, then strawberries and bananas.
Line side and bottom of 3 1/2-quart glass serving bowl with cake slices.
Spoon pudding mixture into prepared bowl.
Cover; chill.
Garnish with additional strawberries and banana slices.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Layer in order in a flat low dish.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.
Serves 14 to 18.

title: jiffy corn dish
directions: Mix together one ingredient at a time.

title: punch
directions: Makes a large amount.

title: sugar-free raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates, then add applesauce, eggs, oil, sweetener and vanilla.
Mix well and blend in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Drained fruit cocktail may be used in place of raisins and water.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll into small balls and press out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 10 dozen cookies.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Put peas and onions in casserole.
Add mushrooms.
Place asparagus on top of this.
Cover with mushroom soup and place in 300° oven until soup melts.
Add layer of cheese.
Place crackers over top and return to oven until brown.

title: green chile quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish with pastry.
Trim excess pastry around edges.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Cook meat until brown and onion until tender.
Sprinkle meat mixture into pastry shell.
Top with green chiles and cheese.
Combine last 4 ingredients, mixing well. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: grilled polenta
directions: Heat the butter; add the garlic and saut until the aroma is released. Add the stock to the pot. Add the cornmeal in a thin stream, whipping constantly to prevent the cornmeal from forming lumps. Continue to whip until the mixture is smooth and cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until the polenta is very thick. Stir the polenta frequently as it cooks. Cover a sheet pan with plastic wrap. Pour the finished polenta onto the sheet pan and level it with a spatula. Cover it with a sheet of parchment paper so that a skin will not form. Cool the polenta to room temperature and then chill under refrigeration. Slice the polenta or cut out into the desired shape (3.5 oz./100 gm per order). Lightly coat with cornmeal before grilling to prevent sticking to grill bars. Grill the polenta on a hot grill just before serving. If necessary, finish reheating the polenta in the oven. Yield: 1/2 hotel pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Boil, peel and chop the shrimp.
Add the next 5 ingredients. Chill.
Serve on your favorite crackers.

title: deep dish cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries; reserve 1 1/2 cups of juice and put cherries aside.
Combine cherry juice, 2/3 cup of sugar and cornstarch in a large saucepan.
Stir and cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Gently stir in cherries, cinnamon and almond extract. Place one pie crust in pan and crease the edges.
Pour in cherry mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Place foil on edges of crust.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Add top crust.
Cut out hearts on top layer.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes more.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in casserole dish and put strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Peel peaches; cut in halves.
Remove stones (you may use more than the 3 peaches if you desire to make larger).
Arrange in pie shell with round sides up.
Mix sugar and flour together; pour over peaches.
Pour on cream; sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 450° oven; reduce to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Canned peaches may be used.

title: prawn and potato omelette
directions: Heat the butter in a 10-inch frying pan.
Stir in the onions and paprika and saute over a moderate heat until the onions are soft.
Add the tomatoes and season to taste.
Cook for about 5 minutes until the mixture is thick and well blended.
Add the potatoes and cook for a few more minutes.
Beat the egg yolks until they are thick and creamy.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until they stand in firm peaks.
Fold the whites and yolks together with a spatula.
Return the frying pan to the heat.
Fold in the prawns and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Fold in the eggs, mixing well. Cook until the eggs are lightly set.
Serve with a green salad.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3/4 cup water.
Add cornstarch mixture to sugar syrup mixture.
Stirring, cook about 10 minutes or until clear. Blend in salt, lemon juice and enough red food coloring to produce light red shade.
Pour prepared glaze over the strawberries and mix gently.
Cool and pour into cooled pie shell.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese on low heat. Gradually add milk and sugar. Beat all together well. Fold in cool whip. Pour in pie shells. Freeze. Serve frozen.

title: alma's lime jello salad
directions: Combine jello, cream cheese, marshmallows and boiling water and let stand.
Drain pineapple.
Add pecans and cherries. Combine with mixture and let stand in refrigerator until firm. Beat 1/2 pint whipping cream and fold into jello mixture.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix vegetables, celery, onion and cheese together.
Add mayonnaise and mix until vegetables are covered.
Place in baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs which have been tossed in butter. Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 15.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking glass pan or round glass pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Mix until liquid.
Pour over batter carefully.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brownies are done.

title: fruit cake bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Add nuts, fruit and extract.
Put in greased flat pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in bars and remove from pan.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon and pour into an iron skillet or baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop the onions and water chestnuts.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Can be served in hollowed out round bread.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients.
Combine last 3 ingredients.
Blend together.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 3 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: a love cake for mother
directions: I have heard them speak of biscuits,

title: peaches 'n' cream pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Place drained peaches on top of filling.
Beat the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons peach juice for 2 minutes.
Spread on top of fruit. Combine the 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350° until a light brown.
Let cool.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel, cut up and boil potatoes until tender and drain.
Mix potatoes, onion and pickles well.
Add mayonnaise and mustard to taste and mix well.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cereal snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in a large baking pan in oven.
Remove pan from oven; stir Worcestershire sauce into melted butter.
Add nuts and cereals and mix well.
Sprinkle with seasonings and stir.
Heat, uncovered, in oven 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Store cooled cereal snack in tightly covered containers.
If snack needs recrisping, reheat in slow oven for a few minutes.

title: ruby chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Brown in butter in skillet.
Add onion, spices, orange rind and orange juice.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add cranberries and walnuts.
Sprinkle with sugar. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ham and potato scallops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice potatoes.
Layer potatoes and onions in buttered casserole dish.
Brown ham; layer on top of potatoes.
Melt butter in skillet you browned ham in.
Add flour; stir in soup and milk.
Simmer; pour over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour.
Top with French fried onions.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cook raisins, Crisco and water 20 minutes and cool to lukewarm. Add vanilla, eggs, soda, sugar, flour and salt.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut while warm.
Pipe white powdered sugar frosting stripes on top when cool.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add egg yolks and vanilla. Add soda to buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, nuts and coconut.
Makes three 9-inch layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: garlic cheese roll
directions: Put ingredients through food chopper.
Mix with cream cheese. Shape into rolls and roll in chili powder.
Wrap with wax paper and chill.
Slice to serve on crackers.
Makes about 3 rolls, 4 1/2 inches long.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream margarine and add sugar and salt alternately with milk until spreading consistency.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Then add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Blend in carrots.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy, about 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually add flour.
Beat just until blended.
Stir in vanilla. Pour into greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing.

title: salad herb blend
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Toss gently with a spoon until blended.
Store in airtight container in a cool, dry place up to six months.
Makes approximately 1 cup.
Sprinkle on salad before adding dressing.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar substitute, butter, eggs, cornstarch and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until well blended and slightly thickened.
Remove from heat, stir in pecans and vanilla and allow filling to cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle raisins on bottom of unbaked pie shell and pour pecan mixture over them.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield: 8 servings, calories per serving 199 plus pie shell calories.

title: cheese fudge
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and cheese.
In a large mixing bowl, stir remaining ingredients into melted mixture.
Mixture will be very thick.
Pat into a slightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate for about 1 hour; cut into squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Saute onion and green pepper in bacon grease.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire to baked beans in baking dish.
Mix.
Add onion, green pepper and crumbled bacon; mix.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: 1 crust apple pie
directions: Peel and dice about 1 1/2 to 2 quarts apples.
Add 1/4 cup water and cook until thick.
Stir often.
Melt oleo.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Beat egg and add sugar and oleo.
Mix well.
Add apples and mix.
Pour in an unbaked 9-inch pie crust and bake. Start oven at 400°, then reduce that to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Place peaches in graham cracker crust.
Mix lemon juice and sweetened condensed milk well.
Pour over peaches.
Cover and refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip just before serving.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first seven ingredients. Spread evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or pan. Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes mixed with melted butter.
Bake for 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cake; mix well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
On top of this mixture, sprinkle the dry cake mix, 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 3/4 cubes of melted margarine. (Do not stir this.)
Put melted margarine on last of all.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip when cool.
Goooood!

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding
mix according to instructions on box.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture. Cover with remaining Cool Whip.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, then milk and beaten egg.
Bake in loaf pan for 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil cleaned out peppers until they change color. Drain. Brown hamburger with onion, salt, pepper and green pepper. Mix with rice and tomato juice. Stuff peppers and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: brownies
directions: Add sugar to eggs; beat.
Melt butter.
Add cocoa.
Add to egg mixture.
Blend in flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: granny's cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling saltwater until tender; drain thoroughly. In large skillet, saut onion in 5 tablespoons butter until tender. Add soup and mix well. Add cheese; heat and stir until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper. Transfer to an ungreased 2-quart baking dish. In a small skillet, melt remaining butter. Cook and stir crumbs in butter until lightly browned; sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: frozen fruit slices
directions: Blend cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in fruits and marshmallows. Fold in whipped cream.
Add a little cherry juice for color. Pour into a 1-quart round container.
Freeze firm (6 hours or overnight).
To serve, slice.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: crunchy fruit bake
directions: In bowl, toss fruit, brown sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon. Transfer to a quart casserole with cover. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Stir fruit. Crush wheat biscuits in plastic bag and add brown sugar and margarine. Sprinkle over fruit mixture; bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes more or until mixture is bubbly around the edge. Cool slightly. Serve with whip topping.

title: country scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish. Dot with butter or margarine, if desired.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.

title: banana coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, oil with milk and sugar together.
Pat into pie pan.
Prick bottom with fork until all dough has been pricked. Bake at 325° until crust is brown.
While crust is cooling, mix 2 packages of pudding and 1 quart milk; cook pudding as directed on package.
Pour pudding into crust and let cool.
Cut up bananas and place on top, then sprinkle with coconut.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Over medium heat, cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa. Bring to boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Add oats, vanilla and peanut butter. Drop by tablespoonsful onto wax paper.

title: apple spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix.
Stir in apples. Pour into greased cake pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake.

title: asparagus in squash rings
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales from stalks with a knife or vegetable peeler, if desired.
Cook asparagus, covered, in boiling water 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
Place squash in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 3 minutes or until tender.
Remove centers of squash slices, leaving 1/4-inch flesh with skin.
Insert 3 to 4 asparagus spears in center of each squash ring; place on a serving platter and set aside.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; beat with mixer until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot, greased skillet.
Cook until golden brown.
Turn once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: nightcap coffee mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl; stir until well blended.
Store in an airtight container.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and chill for at least 6 hours before serving.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix dry jello with Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple and mandarin orange slices.
Refrigerate and serve cold. Serves 8 to 10.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour into greased and floured pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Put in a 2-quart saucepan with 1/4 cup water and salt.
Bring to a good boil; add sugar and butter. Cover and simmer until very tender, about 30 minutes or until it thickens or forms syrup.
Add vanilla.
Do not stir during cooking process.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth; add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to dough; blend in pineapple.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Then mix next 5 ingredients and put in baking dish.
Pour the tomato sauce over the ground beef mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: grilled marinated flank steak
directions: Prick both sides of steak with fork and place in shallow dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over steak.
Cover and marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally. Remove steak from marinade and grill over hot coals for 5 to 7 minutes on each side, or until desired degree of doneness.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix together egg, vinegar and water.
Mix
with dry ingredients.	Chill 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 single crusts.
I usually freeze 2.

title: italian creme fudge
directions: Mix the flour with sugar before adding milk.
Add Karo syrup after milk.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Let cool slightly, then beat.
Add nuts (if desired) and pour in buttered pan.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Add 1/8 to 1/4 cup of mix to 1 cup of boiling water.
Enjoy!

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Beat eggs slightly.
Crush day old bread.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan, slightly buttered.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind all together and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches, generously.
Beat all ingredients with spoon.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.
Let cool for about 10 minutes. Loosen sides of loaf from pan; remove.

title: sausage surprise
directions: Brown sausage and drain (reserve 1 tablespoon of drippings). Saute onion in reserved drippings 3 to 5 minutes. Add sausage, cabbage, carrots
and water.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes. Stir in potatoes.
Cover and cook an additional 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Microwave Directions:
In a microwave baking dish, place butter.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds or until melted.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, onion and seasonings.
Blend well. Transfer to a baking dish.
Cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Mix in Parmesan cheese and green pepper.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 5 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles until done.
Brown hamburger in skillet. Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Place lasagna noodles in roasting pan. Layer spaghetti sauce-ground beef mixture, Mozzarella cheese and noodles, 2 or 3 times, until pan is 3/4 full.
Put in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage.
Separate into leaves.
Mix hamburger, onion, rice, eggs, seasoning and bacon together.
Roll spoonful of mixture in cabbage leaf.
Place in roasting pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar on each layer.
Pour tomato juice over all.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jalapeno cheese loaf
directions: Melt cheeses all together in double boiler.
Cook sausage until brown and crumbly; drain.
Chop peppers, seeds and all, removing only tops.
When cheese is melted, add sausage and peppers.
Pour immediately into large cake pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut into slabs. Wrap in waxed paper.
May refrigerate or freeze.
Keeps well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in water.
Bring to a boil for 2 to 3 minutes. Drain carefully.

title: hard tac candy
directions: Sprinkle baking sheet with powdered sugar.
Mix first 3 ingredients in large pan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until temperature reaches 310°. Remove from heat.
Stir in flavored oil and coloring.
Pour on baking sheet to cool.
When cool, crack in pieces.

title: clothing pre-treatment
directions: Mix in spray bottle.
Good on grease, food spots or dirty collars and cuffs.
After spraying, wash clothing as usual.

title: mardi gras cake
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream shortening.
Add sugars gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add melted butterscotch morsels, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately (add soda and baking powder to last 1/4 cup of flour).
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes. Put filling between layers and on top.
Frost with Seafoam Frosting when cool.

title: mamaw's bible cake
directions: Follow directions of Solomon for bringing up a child, Proverbs 13:24.
Mix and beat all together.
Bake in tube pan, in a 350° oven, for 1 hour.
Can be placed on a plate and frosted with a Heavenly White Frosting.

title: catsup
directions: Mix together; simmer until thick, takes almost an hour. Makes 2 cups.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break or cut angel food cake into small pieces.
In a large bowl or dish layer angel food cake, then strawberries and then mix vanilla pudding and Cool Whip together and put on top of strawberries.
Repeat layers, end with Cool Whip-pudding mixture. If strawberries are in season, they may be used instead of frozen. Also, top with fresh strawberries.

title: squash patties
directions: Let cooked squash drain until all moisture is gone.
Add egg, onion, salt, pepper, flour and cornmeal.
Mix all together.
Drop patties into hot grease until brown.

title: asparagus pasta
directions: In a large skillet, over high heat, saute the mushrooms, green onion and garlic in the olive oil until tender.
Add the olives and tomatoes.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cooked asparagus and dry spices, stirring constantly.
Add Marsala wine to flashpoint, then add chicken stock.
Add cornstarch and water to thicken.
Pour over cooked pasta; mix and sprinkle with Romano.
Serve hot.

title: chicken or pastry puffs
directions: Boil chicken with celery salt.
Drain and cut into small pieces.
Dice and cook vegetables.
Mix soup and milk.
Heat mixture and fold in sour cream and chicken.
Add cooked vegetables to mixtures.
Cook pastry puffs as directed and cut center out. When puffs are brown, top with chicken and vegetables.

title: baked ham souffle
directions: Take crusts off of bread.
Arrange 8 slices of bread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange ham, cheese and remaining bread on top.
Beat eggs; add dry mustard and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Pour over sandwiches.
Refrigerate overnight.
Crush cereal and put on top.
Drizzle oleo over top.
Bake 1 hour at 300° or until done (test like custard).

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, pudding and vanilla in large bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts. Batter will be stiff.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: aunt dora's gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Chill dough (at least 1 hour).

title: tuna asparagus casserole
directions: Place alternate layers of asparagus, tuna, mushroom soup and broken onion rings in casserole; top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Place one drop or to taste of Tabasco sauce in center of green tomato slice; salt and pepper to taste.
Dip in flour and fry to golden brown in oil.

title: monkey cake
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Cut each pack of biscuits into 4 pieces.
Put about 12 squares of biscuits into plastic bag with sugar mixture and shake to coat.
Grease tube or Bundt cake pan.
Put a layer of biscuits in the bottom of pan and pack tight.
Drizzle on some melted butter mixture.
Sprinkle on nuts or raisins.
Continue layers, ending with butter mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Pour in dish or pan and cool until set: the jello, boiling water, blueberries and pineapple.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla, sugar and nuts. Spread over jello.

title: corn custard
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Lightly grease a 1 quart casserole. Melt butter in medium saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and sugar until smooth.
Blend in cream and
milk. Cook,
stirring
over
medium
heat, until mixture boils and is thickened and smooth.
Stir corn into sauce until well-combined and thoroughly blend in eggs.
Turn mixture into prepared casserole.	Set in pan containing 2 inches of water. Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Put beans and onion in a bowl. Bring vinegar, sugar, oil and 1/3 cup bean liquid to a boil.
Pour over beans and onion. Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: no sugar date bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook dates, water and pecans until thick.
Sift dry ingredients; add oats and melted butter.
Spread half mixture in greased pan.
Cover with date mixture; then top with rest of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: stove top stuffing
directions: This recipe is from the memoirs of Mrs. Ruth Hicks, deceased June 14, 1994.

title: round steak dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown floured round steak in oil. Put steak in 9 x 13 casserole. Lay onions over top of steak. Lay potatoes over top of onions. Mix tomato soup and water and pour over top. Cover and bake for 2 hours.

title: honey-mustard vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
When blended, add oil slowly.
Whisk slowly.

title: cranberry dumplings
directions: Put cranberries, sugar and water in saucepan.
Cover and boil until cranberries are cooked.
Make the batter for dumplings by mixing flour, baking powder, salt and enough milk to make a drop batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into the cranberry sauce.
Cover and boil for 20 minutes.

title: maple sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese in a medium bowl.
Form into small balls.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes on 350°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter and saute onions until yellow.
Combine rest of ingredients in a greased 1 3/4 quart casserole dish.
Pour butter and onions on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt margarine.
Cook peppers and mushrooms in margarine until tender. Mix all ingredients in a large baking dish.
Blend well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Beat with rotary beater.
Fold in bread cubes and raisins.
Dot with butter.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown the pork chops in baking dish.
Pour a little water into the pan you browned the chops in and let stand while you arrange casserole.
Slice onion and put slice on each chop with lemon slice, then catsup over with brown sugar.
Add water from pan. Bake in 275° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip with electric mixer until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: You will need 1 brown paper grocery bag.

title: prune, apricot mui
directions: Combine all ingredients except prunes, apricots and li hing mui; boil 3 minutes under low flame and add remaining ingredients. Store in jar and allow to soak 2 to 3 days.

title: pepper steak
directions: In a skillet arrange meat.
Cover with soup mix and tomatoes with the juice.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic powder, pepper and wine.
Simmer covered 1 1/2 hour or until meat is tender.
Thicken juices with cornstarch for gravy.
Green pepper slices may be added halfway through cooking for a firmer texture.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: southwestern pasta sauce
directions: Heat oil over medium heat in large, heavy, non-aluminum saucepan.
Stir in onion and garlic; cook for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Add tomatoes, pepper sauce, salt, cilantro and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until slightly thickened. Place hot, cooked pasta on heated serving platter.
Top with sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: arlie's huevos del diablo
directions: Peel hard-cooked eggs gently.
Cut neatly in halves.
Remove yolks and place into a separate bowl.
Put halved white parts aside to be refilled later.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Mix in corn, pimento and rice.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Add beaten egg.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Combine mixture and pour into prepared pan.
Top with grated cheese and paprika, bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave candy
directions: Melt chips on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in other ingredients. Drop on wax paper.

title: shrimp with peach salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in medium bowl.
Cover and chill.
To assemble plate: Spoon a small mound of peach salsa in center of each plate and arrange the shrimp around the mound. Garnish with lime and cilantro.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar. Let stand overnight. Boil the mixture for 5 minutes or until rhubarb is tender. Stir in Jell-O. Put in jars and seal. This will keep in refrigerator for several months.

title: nancy watson's salad dressing
directions: Mix all this together well and store in refrigerator.

title: chili cheese casserole
directions: Rinse chilies.
Remove seeds and pat dry. Alternate layers of chilies and cheese in buttered baking dish.
Beat eggs with sour cream. Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until puffed and golden. Serve with seasonal fresh fruit and sausages.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and salt. Stir in corn syrup. Gradually add milk. Stir constantly. Cook over medium heat until 245° (firm ball stage). Remove from heat; add vanilla. Pour into buttered pan. Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: black magic cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease 12-cup Bundt pan. In 4-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine butter, syrup and Milky Way bars. Heat 5 to 5 1/2 minutes on Medium, whisking once. Whisk until smooth. Whisk in sugar, then buttermilk, vanilla and eggs. Stir in flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda. Pour batter in pan. Bake 1 hour and 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out almost clean. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Loosen cake from pan; invert onto rack to cool.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Add seasoning and saute. Add soups, Rotel, shrimp, salt and rice.
Bring to a boil for about 1 minute.
Convert to baking dish and cover with foil.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350 degrees.
Open and stir.
Bake another 1/2 hour covered.

title: herb stuffed pork chops
directions: Rub pork chops inside and out with salt and pepper.
Heat butter in a skillet to saute onion and celery.
Remove from skillet; add bread, parsley and milk to onions and celery.
Stuff pork chops with mixture and close with toothpicks.
Heat shortening in skillet and brown on both sides.
Place pork chops in a slow cooker and add wine.
Cook on low heat 8 to 10 hours.

title: seafood gumbo(microwave)
directions: Heat oil in microwave 35 to 45 seconds.
Blend in flour and microwave, uncovered, on High 4 minutes, stirring at half time, until dark brown, not burnt.
Watch carefully as mixture will foam up, hiding color underneath.
Scrape brown roux into microwave-safe 3-quart casserole.
Mix in green onions, garlic, celery and green pepper.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 4 1/2 to 5 minutes until vegetables are soft.
Stir in hot water and undrained tomatoes.
Add bay leaves, salt and red and black peppers.
Cover with lid and microwave on High 10 minutes, stirring at half time.
Add okra; cover and microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes, breaking up frozen clump at half time, until okra is tender-crisp.
Don't overcook okra or it will become gummy. Gently mix in crab and shrimp around edge of casserole, pushing down into sauce.
Cover and microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, rearranging shrimp every few minutes and moving cooked ones to center.
As soon as all shrimp are pink, let gumbo stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Stir in file powder and serve over steamed rice.

title: stir and dump chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and apples; cut broccoli and peel stems using the tender parts.
Cube apples.
Mix with coleslaw dressing to taste.
Chill.
Keeps 2 days in refrigerator.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Blend all ingredients and spread lightly on tortillas.
Roll and refrigerate.
Slice in 1-inch pieces.
Serve as appetizers.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Cook butter, brown sugar, milk and eggs and stir until this comes to a good boil.
Add crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Stir all together.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Spread filling over the crackers.
Cover with more graham crackers.
Cool, then frost with chocolate frosting.

title: coconut pie
directions: Grease 2 pie plates. Mix all ingredients together and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Will make its own crust.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients in covered container and let sit in brine for 1 day.
Serve on endive leaves.
No cooking necessary.

title: krigeli
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
Cut bacon into pieces and fry until crisp.
Pour fat and bacon over potatoes.
Add hot milk. Add beaten eggs, one at a time.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cook 1 hour.
Serve with sour cream.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish beans
directions: Add hamburger to the other ingredients.
Cook for about 2 hours on low heat.	Makes 7 to 10 servings.

title: armenian farmer casserole(meatballs and vegetables)
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Shape into 48 meatballs. Cook in 1 tablespoon butter over medium heat until meatballs are browned.
Transfer to a large (3 1/2-quart) casserole.

title: herb batter bread(low-fat recipe)
directions: Spray a 2-quart casserole dish or a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan generously with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine flour mixture with yeast from foil packet, wheat germ and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in hot water, honey, oil and egg until well mixed (batter will be sticky).
Spread in sprayed casserole dish.
Spray piece of plastic wrap with cooking spray.
Cover batter loosely with sprayed wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in warm place for 45 minutes or until light and doubled in size.
Heat oven to 375°. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from casserole dish.

title: italian filled artichokes
directions: Mix and add enough bread crumbs to make a thick paste.
Trim brown petals and tips on artichokes.
Wash and spread petals apart slightly.
Put filling between petals.
Stand up in pot, half filled with water.
Pour 3 tablespoons olive oil, salt and pepper over them.
Cook about 1 hour.
Pinch with fork; if it goes in easy, they are done.

title: hot apple cider eggnog
directions: Combine cider, sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and egg yolks. Mix in blender until sugar is dissolved.
Add milk to mixture slowly.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Pour milk slowly over egg whites; fold together.
Serve hot topped with whipped cream.
Yields 1 quart.

title: butter crumshus cake
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut 1/4 cup butter into 1/2 cup flour and brown sugar to make a crumb mixture.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare
cake according to directions making 2 (8-inch) layers.
Split
both
layers
horizontally
after	they
have cooled.
Blend sugar, sour	cream
and coconut; chill.
Spread all but one cup of sour cream mixture between the four layers. Blend remaining cup of mixture
with
whipped cream and spread on top of cake.
Seal
in
airtight
container and refrigerate for 3 days. Keep refrigerated after cutting.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix the ingredients in order.
Pour into two well-buttered pie pans.
(You do not need a pie crust.)
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate sugar balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in water.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Shape in 1-inch balls and roll in red or green sugar.
Bake 1-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes or firm to touch.
Cool before removing from pan.
Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: peach delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar, baking powder, vanilla, pecans and soda crackers.
Pour into a buttered 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with topping.

title: summertime slush
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
In nonmetal freezer container, combine dissolved gelatin with remaining ingredients except carbonated beverage; cover.
Freeze until slush consistency, about 8 hours or overnight.
To serve, spoon about 1/2 cup slush into serving glass.
Fill with carbonated beverage. Add vodka or gin, if desired.
Serves 20.

title: meat filling
directions: Mix meats and spinach
with
cheese and let stand.
Fry onion in butter until
onion
is
soft.
Blend all ingredients together and make mounds on dough.

title: lill's californian fajitas
directions: Mix pepper, garlic powder, bay leaves, pineapple juice and soy sauce.
Marinate chicken strips in mixture 8 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Remove chicken strips from marinade.
Place chicken in saute pan with 2 teaspoons of oil.
Cook, stirring frequently about 4 to 5 minutes.
While chicken is cooking, add vegetables to marinade.
Remove from marinade and add to chicken in pan.
Cook all together until chicken is cooked through.
Discard marinade. Fajitas can be served plain or folded in a warm flour tortilla. Serve with salsa.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: chart house mud pie
directions: Mix crushed chocolate wafers and melted butter together thoroughly.
Press mixture into a 9 inch pie plate.
Cover with soft coffee ice cream.
Top with cold fudge sauce.
(Put fudge sauce in the freezer for a while to make spreading easier.) Freeze for approximately 10 hours before serving.
8 servings.

title: papillotte de st.  jaques a la julienna de legumes(scallops with julienne of vegetables)
directions: Peel and wash vegetables.
Julienne vegetables and blanch. Slice the scallops.
Add vegetables and lemon.
Wrap in foil.
Cook in oven on high heat for four minutes.
Pour melted butter over all and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork in soy sauce
directions: Fry pork in hot oil until brown. Add onions, green onions and garlic.
Fry until brown. Add ginger, brown sugar, soy sauce, 1/2 cup water and salt. Be careful how much salt as soy sauce is salty. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Fill the filler lined basket of a large automatic percolator with the brown sugar, cloves, allspice and cinnamon sticks. Prepare as you would coffee according to manufacturer's directions, but substitute cider for water.
Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain cans of pineapple and oranges.
Put juice in saucepan; add sugar and cornstarch.
Boil until thick; cool.
Mix in pineapple tidbits, mandarin oranges and bananas.
Refrigerate.

title: marinated chinese vegetables
directions: Drain all vegetables and mix in a bowl.
Heat all vinegar wines, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until sugar is melted.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate 24 hours and stir during this time.
Keep in a bowl with lid.
This is very good and lasts up to two weeks.

title: eclair cake
directions: Melt margarine in the water.
Beat in the flour and eggs. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt and cheese.
Combine milk, egg and zucchini.
Add to dry ingredients. Mix just until moistened.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well and put in a large casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally, during baking.
Remove cover and spoon accumulated fat from top of casserole.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add cherry juice and vanilla.
Stir together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in coconut, nuts, dates and cherries. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: layer potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water.
Pare and slice and arrange 1/3 of the slices in a greased baking dish.
Over the slices of potatoes, place the sliced eggs and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with half the sour cream.
Make another layer of potato slices, then one of ham, then cover with rest of the sour cream.
Finish with a final layer of potatoes.
Top with the crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Add the heavy cream.
Bake in hot oven at 450°
for 30 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook 1 pound pasta.
While pasta is cooking, mix together olive oil, wine vinegar, dill, garlic cloves, salt and pepper.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt in large cake pan margarine and shortening.
Coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Place coated chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Turn chicken over and bake 30 more minutes.
Do not cover chicken.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Beat 4 to 5 minutes.
Drop from spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender and add water, chicken, carrots, bouillon, marjoram, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes in 10-inch tube pan.

title: dr. pepper fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until sugar and chocolate are dissolved.
Continue on low-medium heat until 236° or soft ball.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm (110°).
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until it loses its shine.
Add nuts; pour into buttered square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs on medium speed.
Stir in mix, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, frost, cut and refrigerate.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add brown sugar and mix.
Put bread in pan in three layers.
Do not use crust.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a saucepan; cook on low heat to soft ball stage.
In a warm bowl, mix marshmallow cream, vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour hot syrup into this mixture and stir until well blended.
Pour onto a greased platter.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix 3 packages raspberry Jell-O and 3 1/2 cups hot water.
Add 1 can blueberries and 1 can crushed pineapple.
Let chill until it congeals.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat the soup and add the cream cheese.
Add the gelatin mixed with 1/4 cup water and cool.
Add celery, onion, mayonnaise and shrimp.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set, at least for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: "gooey butter cake"
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs, stirring until well blended. Spread batter into greased 13 x 9 pan. Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in remaining 2 eggs, then vanilla. Set aside 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Beat in remaining powdered sugar. Pour over cake mix. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake pulls away from pan. Cool 20 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining powdered sugar.

title: acini de pepe macaroni salad
directions: Drain fruit and save juices.
Mix 1 3/4 cups juices with sugar, flour, salt, eggs and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until creamy but not thick.
Cook 1/2 box macaroni in water and oil; drain.
Pour fruit sauce over macaroni and let it set for several hours or overnight.
Mix well and fold in marshmallows, coconut and Cool Whip.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Place apples in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and almond extract.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix flour, baking powder, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup brown sugar and salt into a mixing bowl. Cut in 1/4 cup butter until the mixture is slightly coarser than cornmeal.
Combine egg and milk, pour over the dry ingredients, stir just enough to combine and spoon it over the apples in the baking dish.

title: no bean chili
directions: Saute the onion and peppers in oil in Dutch oven. Add beef. Cook until brown, stirring to crumble meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Top with grated cheese.

title: banana slush
directions: Combine water and sugar and bring to boil and cook 5 minutes. Remove from stove and put in large bowl.
Add orange juice, water and juice of lemon.
Add pineapple, bananas, raspberries or strawberries and oranges.
Mix together well.
Put into large loaf pan, 9 x 13-inch and freeze until ready to use.
Remove 1 hour before you are ready to serve.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix cottage cheese, drained fruit and jello (powdered).
Add Cool Whip.
Mix and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Mix together brown sugar and dry pudding mix.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Pour melted butter over top.
Place uncovered on counter overnight.
In morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and turn onto plate.
Use spatula to scrape excess topping from pan.
Scrape onto rolls.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: mother k. cookies
directions: Mix lard and sugar, then add eggs to the sour milk; add the soda and stir.
Then add to the sugar mixture and then the flour. Just add enough flour so that you can handle dough.
(I never roll out the dough.
I pat it out and use cookie cutter.)
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These are better when left kinda thick.

title: tomato pecan salad
directions: Boil tomato soup; mix in a small amount of cream cheese at a time with the tomato soup.
Dissolve the Jell-O in the boiling water.
Mix these two mixtures together.
Add the remaining ingredients, mix together.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: crab meat pasta salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Can be mixed in blender on grate.
Do not overblend.

title: barbecue steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place steaks in marinade and refrigerate 24 hours.
Turn meat after 12 hours.
Grill to desired doneness.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown ground chuck and pork sausage, then drain.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on slices of rye bread.
Place slices on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in airtight bag and store in freezer until needed.
To serve, bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and drain the hamburger, along with the garlic, onions and salt and pepper.
Pour hamburger mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine vegetables and soup; pour over the hamburger mixture. Layer package of Tater Tots over the vegetables; top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry angel delight
directions: Tear cake to measure 8 cups.
Place half in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Reserve 1/3 of pie filling; spread remaining over cake.
Top with remaining cake.
Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream; spoon over cake.
Cover and chill.
Spoon remaining cherries to serve.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
Fold in remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Put 1/2 of the mixture in a serving dish and refrigerate until firm.
Top with sour cream and put on remainder of mixture.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: sun tea
directions: Fill jug with water.
Put in 10 tea bags.
Put jug in the sun for about 6 hours (more or less, depending on how light or dark you prefer).
After the tea sits in the sun, take tea bags out. Put 1 1/2 cups sugar (or less) in the tea.
Mix well.
Put in 4 thin slices of lemon, if preferred.

title: simple but delicious subs
directions: Brown hamburger meat and chopped onion.
Pour off excess grease.
Return to heat and add 1 cup barbecue sauce.
Allow this to mix and warm thoroughly.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve lemon jello, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Chill until thick, about 1 1/2 hours.
Chill evaporated milk (overnight, if possible).
Chill bowls and beaters.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Remove heads from shrimp, but do not peel.
Clean and wash shrimp and drain.
On top of stove in a Dutch oven pot, put olive oil and saute onion and garlic.
When softened, add shrimp, then distribute salt over all and shake out 1/2 of the bottle of Louisiana hot sauce.
Mix everything together and cook on hot flame for 5 minutes in covered pot.
Turn off and let set about 5 minutes.

title: boysenberry cobbler
directions: Put berries on bottom and batter on top.
If fresh berries, put them on top.
Cook in buttered Pyrex dish until brown and bubbling. Serve warm.

title: breakfast enchiladas
directions: Brown and drain pork sausage.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until eggs are done.
Cover tortillas and heat in microwave oven until just warm.
(Do not overheat).
Place egg mixture on tortilla and roll up.
Salsa may be served also.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Cover with towel and allow to rise for a few
hours.
Cook and drain broccoli.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown chops in electric frypan.
Pour off any fat.
Add can of soup and 1/2 can of water.
(Mix soup and water before adding.) May double soup and water if you want extra gravy for potatoes. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk to form dough.
Roll into rectangle. Mix sausage and cheese together.
Spread mixture over dough.
Roll dough up from long side.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Slice and bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Cook dressing.
Take the sliced turkey and roll dressing in the turkey slices to make a roll.
Pour gravy over rolls and bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or microwave for 10 minutes.

title: deviled drumsticks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Coat the bottom of a large baking dish with 1 tablespoon oil.
