Combine mustard, dill, salt and pepper.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs.
Coat drumsticks with mustard mixture, then roll in cheese mixture.
Put in baking dish and drizzle with remaining oil.
Cook until golden brown in preheated oven, about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cake icing
directions: Mix all ingredients before pecans, then after all are mixed, add the pecans.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with sugar.
Cover and refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes.
Just before serving, whip cream until stiff. Gently stir in orange juice.
Fold in berries, or serve individually, in small bowls topped with the flavored cream. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mary bessey's easy yeast rolls
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Let set until yeast starts to foam.
Add egg and 2 cups flour.
Mix well and add another 2 cups flour.
Do not knead.
Cover and let rise until about double in bulk.
Turn onto floured board and knead into rolls.
Put in a 12 x 8-inch greased pan.
Let rise until double in bulk and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: chocolate nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: christmas morning casserole
directions: Butter a 7 x 10-inch casserole dish.
In one bowl, mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, mix bread and cheese.
Place cheese and bread in casserole dish.
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop an inch or more apart on a cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Bake at 400°.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, water and egg.
Bake on hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn when bubbles appear.

title: bar-be-que beans
directions: Cut up	bacon
and
fry with onion.
Drain and mix with other ingredients.
Bake	in covered casserole or baking dish. Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: au gratin carrots
directions: Cook the carrots until crisp-tender; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan over medium heat, saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 minute or until thickened.
Stir in the cheese just until melted.
Add carrots and parsley.
Pour into a greased 8 inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle cornflakes over carrots.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: "old timey" hot chocolate
directions: Heat chocolate and water in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk. Heat just until hot (do not boil).
Beat with hand beater until foamy or stir until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Serves about 6 (1 cup each).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Use a mixer as it mixes better.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dudsedia
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash, dry and season chicken; set aside.
Wash and drain rice.
Boil celery and carrots for 2 minutes; save the water.
Saute the onions with Crisco.
Add paprika to change color.
Add rice, chicken, celery and carrots. Add enough water to cover the chicken.
Put in oven for 1/2 hour. Add tomatoes and juice.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Place sausage in bowl and mix with regular Cheddar cheese. Cut peppers in half lengthwise and remove stem and seeds.
To reduce spicy heat of peppers, they may be rinsed and soaked in vinegar overnight.
Stuff pepper halves with sharp Cheddar cheese. Pat out a scoop of meat and wrap around pepper; shape into an oval.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until meat is baked.
May be served hot or cold.
Freezes well.

title: southern cheese grits
directions: Beat melted butter into grits.
Beat eggs well and add to the grits.
Add light cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend well. Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour mixture into dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Microwave 15 minutes on High; stir.
Cook for 13 minutes.* Stir and add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir until ready to pour.
Add 1 to 2 cups of pecans.
Drop on wax paper.

title: south carolina sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in quarters and boil until tender.
Remove skins and mash.
Combine hot sweet potatoes approximately 3 cups with next 5 ingredients and beat well.
Put potatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: clay (for play)
directions: Combine ingredients, one at a time, as listed:
flour, salt, oil, alum, water and food coloring.
Knead like dough until well mixed and pliable.
Store in plastic bags to help it stay moist and last longer.
If it dries out, add water a few drops at a time.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Grease a 9 X 9 pan.
Cream shortening and sugar together; add eggs and apples.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Double the recipe for a 9 X 13 pan and bake for a longer time.

title: chocolate bit drop cookies
directions: Cream
sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly. Spoon flour into dry measuring cup.
Pour measured flour onto wax paper. Add
soda
and salt to flour.
Stir to blend.
Add dry ingredients to
creamed mixture, mix well.
Stir in chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: cream dessert
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Then fold it in.
Put in pie shell and chill.

title: corn bread
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg; add meal, flour, sugar, cheese, milk and set aside.
Preheat oven to 450° with 1/4 cup oil in iron skillet.
After preheat is ready, pour oil in bowl of meal mixture.
Mix fast and well.
Sprinkle cornmeal in bottom of skillet to keep from sticking.
Then pour mixture into skillet and bake about 30 minutes or until golden brown and sides leave skillet.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Divide in half.
Pour first half into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked zucchini fans
directions: Slice each zucchini lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices, taking care not to cut through the stem ends.
Place zucchini fans in a lightly greased shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Brush butter mixture over sliced zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender, basting occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frosty red punch
directions: Chill Tropical Kool-Aid.
Add water.
Add Hawaiian Punch and 7-Up.
Then add red sherbet.

title: ropa vieja
directions: Boil meat in 1 cup water with bay leaf.
When tender, put aside until cooled.
Saute garlic, onion and pepper.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer half hour.
Shred meat into strings and put into tomato mixture.
Add water from meat.
Cool half hour more.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve with white rice.

title: sugar free chocolate fudge
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, chocolate, sweetener and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 8-inch baking pan lined with foil.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa in saucepan over low heat.
Mix flour, sugar and slightly beaten eggs.
Add to cocoa mixture, salt and vanilla.
Pour in pan or uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm to touch.
Watch carefully.
Do not overcook (about 25 minutes) so it will be "fudgy" inside.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take meat off bones; cut in bite sized pieces.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Cut tortillas in fourths or sixths; dip in hot Crisco and remove quickly.
Put layer of tortillas on bottom of buttered casserole. Add onion and soup mix, then layer of chicken.
Repeat layers until dish is full.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in one layer of pan.
Mix preserves, dressing and soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste occasionally.
Prepare rice.
Stir parsley into rice.
Serve with chicken and sauce.

title: poached cod with mushroom sauce
directions: In large nonstick skillet, cook
mushrooms in margarine over medium-high heat until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in salt, pepper, wine and water.
Gently add frozen fillets to skillet; cover.
Cook over medium-high heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Turn fillets once during cooking.
Remove fillets to serving platter.
Keep warm.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.

title: sheryl's flat bread
directions: Mix together oatmeal, white and graham or wheat flour, baking powder, salt and sugar if you choose.
Work in oleo like pie crust and then add buttermilk with baking soda.
Roll out real thin. Place on cookie sheet.
I make it in 9-inch round portions and bake them in 350° oven for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream oil and sugar well.
Add dry ingredients, eggs, fruits, nuts, vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: golden pumpkin pickles
directions: Tie spices in double thick cheesecloth.
Combine sugar and vinegar in a large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat a little and put in spice bag.
Boil about 5 minutes.
Add pumpkin pieces and cook over medium heat until tender.
Remove spice bag.
Spoon hot pumpkin into hot, sterile jars.
Cover with hot syrup.
Seal at once.
Yields 5 pints.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Combine 1 cup prepared whipped topping with vanilla pudding, pumpkin, milk and spices.
Mix slowly with rotary beater just until blended, about 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell. Chill until set, at least 2 hours.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.

title: almond cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Press with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs.
Put vinegar in milk and add to butter mixture. Sift dry ingredients and add to butter mixture with fruit and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients, except strawberries, until a soft dough forms.
Spread in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or round 8 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into serving pieces. Put strawberries on top.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: amy's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Mix corn, onions, soup and garlic powder.
Put into bottom of a baking dish.
Cook potatoes and place on top of hamburger mix.
Place cheese on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon; remove bacon from pan.
Cook peppers, celery and onion in bacon grease.
Drain.
Cook potatoes in chicken broth until tender.
Add bacon, peppers, celery and onion.
Puree one package corn in blender.
Add puree and other package to potato mixture.
Add milk and ham.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and butter.

title: tuna mold
directions: Soak gelatin in 3/4 cup water for 5 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin (after soaking) over hot water in a double boiler or use 2 saucepans.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add gelatin; stir well.
Pour into mold.
Chill 2 hours.
Unmold. Delicious served as spread on crackers.

title: crawfish corn bread
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon oil until tender.
Remove from the heat.

Stir in jalapenos; set aside. In a bowl, combine cornmeal, baking powder, salt and baking soda. In another bowl, beat the eggs, milk and remaining oil; stir into the dry ingredients just until blended.
Stir in the corn, cheese, green onions, crawfish and reserved jalapeno mixture.
Pour into a greased 13x9x2-inch baking pan.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and garlic.
Add soups and refried beans; stir.
Add olives, mushrooms, sour cream and salsa.

title: puffing crab or chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased 9x13 pan with 1/2 the bread slices. In a dish combine the meat, onion, celery, peppers, mayonnaise and salt and pepper.
Pour over bread.
Place remaining bread on top. Beat eggs and milk together and pour over second layer of bread. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Before baking, pour soup over the top, sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake uncovered 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.

title: bean and turkey soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large Dutch oven; bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
9 1/2 cups.
Can be frozen up to 6 months.
Thaw in refrigerator 8 hours, then cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.

title: festive nonalcoholic fruit punch
directions: Mix water, fruit juice concentrates and mashed bananas in a large bowl.
Blend thoroughly with a whisk.
Pour into 8 or 9 (1 pint) containers and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 1 hour before serving.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, egg, crumbs and water.
Roll into balls. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
In a saucepan mix ingredients (chili sauce, 1/2 cup grape jelly and 2 tablespoons lemon juice).
Heat until bubbly.
Add meatballs and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Slice sweet potatoes and add salt.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until sticky.
Cover top with small marshmallows and brown lightly.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Crush pretzels in food processor.
Add melted butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: turkey noodle bake
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, stir together soup and milk.
Add turkey, cheese and onion; mix well.
Stir in uncooked noodles. Pour water over mixture.
Top with crumbs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Drain and add next 4 ingredients to mixture.
Add coconut and pecans; mix thoroughly. Chill overnight.

title: cloud-nine cream
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Gradually add reserved juice; beat until smooth.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Fold in cream cheese, pineapple, sugar, pecans and cherries.
Cover.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Scrape carrots and cut on diagonal, making slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Cook in salted water until tender, but still crisp.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Mix onion, horseradish, mayonnaise or salad dressing, salt, pepper and carrot liquid.
Combine with carrots into buttered casserole.
Mix the bread crumbs with the melted butter. Spread over carrots and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 6.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Mix all together.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 325°.
After 1/2 hour, mix and the last 15 minutes sprinkle chow mein noodles on and bake 15 minutes longer (1/2 can chow mein noodles).

title: dutch chocolate cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine cocoa with boiling water, mixing well. Let cool completely.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour 3 (9-inch) pans.
Sift flour with soda, salt and baking powder; set aside.

In large bowl at high speed, beat butter with sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes. At lower speed, add flour mixture in fourths, alternating with cocoa mixture in thirds, beginning and ending with flour.
Do not overbeat.
Pour in pans and bake 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
Add mayonnaise, applesauce and relish.
Use 6-cup mold.
Chill until well set.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add melted shortening.
Knead and roll out.
Shape into rolls and let set for about 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm with butter or syrup, jam or honey.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Mix cocoa, food coloring and hot coffee together in small bowl.
Add to mix.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.

title: peanut salad dressing
directions: Mix well and let stand for a few hours in the refrigerator before
using.

title: no fail dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Break egg into 1 cup measure and fill with milk to 1 cup.
Beat lightly and add to dry ingredients.
Beat together.
Let stand for 5 minutes to rise.
Drop batter by tablespoon on top of boiling stew or soup.
Cover and boil 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Mix cream cheese (softened) with sugar and milk. Using mixer blend very well 2 or 3 minutes. Add vanilla. Then add cool whip and mix well, pour in crust. Top with fresh strawberries.

title: parmesan risotto
directions: Heat stock in saucepan over medium heat; keep at a low simmer.
Heat olive oil in a heavy-bottomed saucepan over medium heat.
Add shallots to oil, and cook, stirring, until translucent. Add rice.
Cook, stirring, until rice begins to make a clicking sound like glass beads, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Mix oats, flour, brown sugar, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg. Layer in microwavable dish the apples, mixture, apples and mixture.
Bake in microwave on High for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: potato fritters
directions: Boil the potatoes; peel them and put through a sieve or mash while still hot.
Add eggs, butter, flour and salt.
Knead.
Flour the board well.
Roll out until 5/8-inch thick.
With a small cookie cutter (which should be dipped into flour after each use), cut rounds and fry them in hot oil.
Serve with some sauce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: karen cheatham's hot cinnamon fruit
directions: Drain and reserve juice of pineapple chunks, pear halves, peach halves and apricot halves.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix onion and cream cheese and spread on ham; then roll up and cut into pieces.
Place toothpicks in each, if desired.

title: congealed mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain and chop water chestnuts.
Drain pineapple and oranges, reserving juices.
Add enough water to juices to make 1 1/2 cups. Dissolve Jell-O in hot tea; add juices.
Chill until consistency of egg white.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and chestnuts.
Put in lightly oiled 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm and unmold on lettuce. Serves 8.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peanuts, in a heavy saucepan (1 1/2-quart).
Stir and bring to full boil.
Lower heat and keep stirring while mixture boils slowly for 3 minutes.
Take off heat; stir in all at once the peanuts.
Beat until candy starts to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Makes about 24 clusters.
Pecans may be substituted for peanuts.

title: spinach dip in onion rye bread
directions: Thaw and drain frozen spinach (should be almost dry).
Mix with rest of ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool, then frost.

title: lo-cal chip dip
directions: Place cottage cheese in blender; blend until smooth.
Add soup mix; add enough milk to make dipping consistency.

title: canned okra
directions: Cover with water.
Put on stove and heat until it changes color.
Put in hot jar and seal. When you are ready to use, rinse with cold water and drain.
Batter and fry like fresh okra.

title: coffee roll
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour, egg and sour cream.
Chill for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together the cinnamon, sugar and chocolate chips.
Beat together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in sour cream.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put 1/2 of the batter in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the cinnamon, sugar and chocolate chip mixture.
Put remaining batter on top, then remaining cinnamon, sugar and chocolate chip mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Line sides and bottom of spring-form pan with ladyfingers. Combine chocolate bits, sugar and 1/2 cup cold water over low heat. Stir until melted and beat until smooth.
Cool slightly and add vanilla.
In a large bowl, beat egg yolks slightly.
Gradually, add chocolate mixture until thick.
Beat 8 egg whites until stiff. Fold beaten egg whites in chocolate mixture with spatula.
Spread over first layer of ladyfingers and repeat until mixture is used. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Can be made the day before also.
This is a rich, delicious dessert, easy to make.

title: bulgogi (neobiani)
directions: Cut the tenderloin into about 1/2-inch thick slices. Tenderize by making small incisions lengthwise and crosswise. Mix the other ingredients together and apply to the meat, slice by slice. Marinate the beef for 30 minutes and broil both sides on a pre-heated iron grill. It is better to broil quickly on a high heat. Serve with powdered pine nuts on top.

title: hot rolls
directions: Add enough flour to make dough like a biscuit dough. Use plain flour only. Let this stand overnight. Roll out and make your rolls.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze as much of the water out of the spinach as possible. Then add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute between each.
Add flour, cinnamon and cloves; blend.
Add baby food.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Bake in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients while broccoli cooks.
Place in oblong 2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted margarine and place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat with onion and green pepper. Drain any grease.
Add tomatoes, chopped (2 cups) and taco mix. Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
In bowl, combine cottage cheese, 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese and eggs.
In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, arrange 3 tortillas on bottom of sprayed dish.
Spoon meat evenly over tortillas.
Top with 3 more tortillas, then cheese mixture. Bake covered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover, check that cheese mix is done.
Sprinkle with cheese (1/2 cup left) and bake uncovered 5 more minutes until cheese melts.
Remove from oven. Let sit 5 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes and serve.
Yum! Yum!
Easy!

title: apple streusel pie
directions: Combine Equal, cornstarch, lemon juice, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg. Sprinkle over apples in large bowl. Toss to coat. Spoon apples into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.

title: homemade catsup
directions: Place contents of one can of tomatoes in blender container; cover and process on medium speed for 30 to 40 seconds, or until smooth.
Repeat with each can.
In a large saucepan, combine tomatoes with all remaining ingredients except Sweet 'N Low. Simmer, uncovered, until sauce is reduced and thickened, 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir in sweetener.
One tablespoon has 6 calories.

title: round red devils
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature, then add ham.
Chill, then roll in balls about size of a teaspoon.
In a medium size bowl, place chopped pecans and drop balls into bowl.
Shake gently about 6 balls at a time to cover with nuts.
Keep refrigerated until time to serve.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: out of this world candy
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let set for 1 hour, then melt 1 bar paraffin and 12 ounces chocolate chips (usually I use two of each).
Keep hot while dipping candy.

title: easy hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cook slowly in double boiler or microwave for four minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs (one at a time). Add flour, alternating with sour cream; beat after each addition. Add soda and salt; beat well, then add flavorings. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: Brown beef and mix in taco seasoning; set aside.
Mix together biscuit mix and water.
On floured board, knead 20 times.
Spread dough into greased pizza pan.
Spread dough with pizza sauce, then top with meat, then other ingredients in order and end with cheeses.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pizza is thick.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over carrots.

title: baked crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except mayonnaise and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Turn into casserole.
In a small bowl, blend mayonnaise and egg yolks.
Spread on crab mixture.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peppermint ice cream cake
directions: Cut angel food cake into 3 layers.
Soften ice cream.
Chop chocolate patties.
Add with nuts to ice cream.
Spread between layers of cake.
Spread top and sides of cake with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Place in freezer.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados; mix with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Layer in order:
beans, avocados, sour cream, onion, tomatoes, olives and cream cheese.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend together.
Mix at medium speed for 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix all together.
Let stand overnight.
Slowly boil for 5 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Mix cornstarch and paprika in plastic bag.
Put in chicken to coat.
Brown chicken in skillet with 1/2 cup oil.
Put in roasting pan with drippings.
Bake 2 hours at 225°, then put celery, peppers and pineapple on chicken.
Cook 1 hour.
Mix rest of cornstarch, soy sauce and pineapple juice.
Pour over chicken. Cook another hour.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: "ton" cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed.
Let cool completely.
Slice sheet cake horizontally (in half).
Mix instant pudding and use as filling between layers.
Open pie filling and spread on top layer evenly.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pie filling.
Sprinkle with nuts and add cherries to decorate.
Taste resembles "bee sting" cake!
Enjoy!

title: microwave grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Put cheese between 2 slices of bread.
Place in microwave. Set for 20 seconds on High.
Take out of microwave.
If by chance you cannot chew, you must have pressed 2 minutes.
(An extra 0!) Go back to step one and begin again.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
Use 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons of mixture per 8 ounce cup boiling water.
Enjoy a cup with a friend.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Combine olive oil, lemon juice, mint, salt, pepper and garlic in a shaker; cover and shake well.
Let stand at room temperature for about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine bulgar wheat and boiling water.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Drain well, squeezing out excess water.
Add celery, parsley, onions, cucumber and plum tomato.
Pour dressing on and toss.
Refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.

title: italian cookies
directions: *Vanilla or lemon flavoring may be substituted for anise.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix
all ingredients together using only 1/4 cup tomato sauce. Shape
into
loaf;
brown	in
pressure pan to which a small amount of oil has been added.
Pour rest of tomato sauce and add 1
cans
of
water
around meat.
Pressure at 10 pounds about 30 minutes.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Form into ball and refrigerate. Mix the rest of ingredients and pour over ball before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix carrots, green pepper and onion; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrot mixture and mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: green grape salad
directions: Mix sour cream and brown sugar.
Add grapes to mixture until grapes are well covered.
Place in covered dish and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Great dish for summer luncheon.

title: candied yams
directions: Slice potatoes and lay in large frying pan.
Add other ingredients on top of potatoes.
Put lid on and start on high heat until lid is hot to touch.
Turn heat down and cook until potatoes are tender and slightly brown.

title: hot cinnamon sparkle
directions: Combine pineapple juice, cinnamon candies and grenadine syrup in a medium saucepan.
Heat, stirring until candies melt and mixture is hot.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into mugs and serve warm.

title: sauteed aqua
directions: Place saucepan filled with tap water on heating element of kitchen stove or Pyrex bowl in microwave oven.
Turn heating device on high temperature setting.
As water begins to have turbulence, stir occasionally with wooden spoon.
Be sure to watch carefully as water level will gradually become lower.
Soon after water completely disappears, the saucepan will begin to turn brown.
At this point, you have sauteed aqua, more commonly known as burned water.
This recipe highly recommended for new brides.

title: italian sausage loaf
directions: Roll dough out on floured board into an 18 x 6-inch rectangle. Spread the remaining ingredients over dough.
Roll up jelly roll style.
Transfer to greased cookie sheet and form into a ring. Pinch closed all edges.
Mix egg and 1 teaspoon milk and brush on filled bread ring.
With a sharp knife make slashes on top of ring, 1 1/2-inches apart.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Leftovers may be placed in the fridge and eaten cold.

title: round steak "fingers"
directions: Cut a large round steak into finger strips, about the size of your baby finger.
This is done fastest using kitchen scissors. Dip each piece into a pan containing one beaten egg and a little evaporated milk.
Then dip into pan with flour or shake in a paper bag containing flour until coated.
Salt and pepper.
Fry in oil or bacon drippings until brown and crunchy.
Gravy can be made from drippings; serve over rice or potatoes.

title: easy tuna dish
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed adding a little extra milk.
Saute onions, green pepper in 2 to 3 tablespoons butter and add to macaroni.
Also add tuna, soup and mushrooms.
Cook until hot.
May be cooked in microwave.

title: quarkkroketten
directions: Mix the curd cheese, sour cream, lemon rind, egg and milk-enough to make a batter.
Dissolve the yeast in warm milk and add to the batter . Add raisins.
With floured hands, form little kroketts (balls) and let them rest a while.
Deep fry until golden brown and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: one 'n one casserole
directions: Brown beef in a skillet; drain off excess fat.
Put in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with rice and onion soup mix.
Combine mushroom soup and boiling water.
Pour over rice. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender. Sprinkle with onion tops.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crunch
directions: Blend baking mix, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and butter.
Let cool.

title: garden cheese soup
directions: In large kettle, cook celery and onion in margarine unti tender; stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water, then bouillon, pepper and vegetables; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot (do not boil).
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, onions, Worcestershire sauce, milk and 1/2 of chopped beef.
Mix well and roll into ball, then roll in rest of chopped beef.
Chill and serve.

title: deluxe rhubarb pie
directions: Beat until stiff.
Bake in 350° oven until brown, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom of greased baking dish with half of the noodles, then a layer of chicken, then celery and onions.
Use entire amount of chicken, onions and celery.
Pour chicken soup, thinned with milk, over this.
Cover with remaining noodles and cashew nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well
after
each
addition. Combine flour, soda and salt in separate
bowl.
Mix
together sour
cream and chopped peaches. Fold
dry
ingredients
into creamed mixture
alternately
with sour
cream
and
peaches, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Stir in vanilla and almond extract.
Pour batter into greased
and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake for 75 to 80 minutes at
or until cake tastes done.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat.
Add flour with spices and salt.
Mix.
Add applesauce, then fruit and nuts.
Mix 1 teaspoon soda with 2 tablespoons boiling water.
Add to batter and stir.
Makes 2 dozen medium sized cupcakes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Boil spaghetti.
Mix and pour into casserole.
Bake at 300° about 1 hour.

title: lo-cal strawberry jello salad
directions: Crust:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine together and press into 8-inch square pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils well.
Saute vegetables in butter about 5 minutes, then add lentils, stock and seasonings.
Cook slowly for an hour or until lentils are done.
Add tomato paste and it's ready to serve.
Garnish each soup bowl serving with some minced green onions.

title: hearts of palm spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 9-inch quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 2 cups.

title: hominy and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: surprise peach pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add milk and peaches. Spread in well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine
cream cheese, pineapple, onion and seasoned salt. Mix well, add 1 cup of pecans.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Great!

title: corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease
bottoms
only
of 12 muffin cups. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cups; level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour,
corn	meal,
sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Stir in	bacon and corn.
In small bowl, combine milk, oil and
egg.
Blend
well.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients
until	dry ingredients are moistened. Fill prepared muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake for 18 to 23 minutes (or until golden brown).
Cool
minute.
Remove
from
pan. Serve warm.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in milk overnight.
Cream butter and sugar. Add poppy seed and milk, then flour and vanilla last.
Beat 3 minutes and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 layers in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar and flour.
In saucepan, mix butter, cocoa, water and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix with electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured jelly pan.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all together. Bake in a large pan (approximately 9 x 13-inch) in a 350° oven for approximately 40 minutes.

title: sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Beat egg yolks, water, sugar, vanilla and flour until a good sponge forms (about 4 minutes at medium speed).
Fold in whites at low speed. Bake in an ungreased tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Invert pan about 20 minutes before removing cake.
Cover with powdered sugar.

title: cranberry cottage pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Add slightly beaten egg. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Add cranberries last. Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°. For a double recipe, use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: church windows
directions: Melt all of chocolate chips and stick of oleo in a double boiler; cool.
Pour over marshmallows.
Add nuts and mix. Sprinkle coconut onto 3 sheets of wax paper.
Shape and roll into logs.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: spicy shrimp and sausage over creamy grits
directions: Shell shrimp and set aside.
Cut sausage into bite-sized pieces and saute until nearly done.
Pour off fat.
Add sausage to simmering chicken stock.
Make a roux, slowly browning flour in butter.
Add some of stock to roux and stir, then add this back to stockpot to thicken it slightly.
Add salt, file powder and more spices if necessary.
Add shrimp to stock mixture and cook until pink (3 to 5 minutes).
Cook grits a bit dry.
Remove from heat and fold in whipped cream.
Pour shrimp and sausage mixture over grits in warmed bowls.
Serve with salad and French bread.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush 20 Oreo cookies and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and
chocolate.
Keep on low heat and add
eggs.
Stir until thick.
Add powdered sugar (on heat) and beat well by hand.
Pour mixture on cookies and freeze at least one hour.
Soften ice cream.
Stir in creme de menthe.
Pour over chocolate layer.
Crush 5 more cookies. Sprinkle on top and freeze overnight (at least).

title: bumbie's banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together and add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 3 one-pound coffee cans and fill about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool; replace plastic lids on cans and freeze.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender; let cool.
Debone and cut in cubes. Save broth.
Take 2 cups of broth and thicken like light gravy.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients adding half and half last.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a 9-inch square pan with fork, mix well the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add carrots, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix briskly with fork until thoroughly blended.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until pick comes clean and cake pulls away from pan.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: hoppin' john
directions: In a large soup kettle or dutch oven, combine first four ingredients.
Allow to simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, butter, cocoa and peanut butter in a heavy saucepan and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla and nuts and beat 4 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper to cool and harden.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in peelings.
Put in freezer or refrigerator until very cold.
Peel and grate.
Add cheese, sour cream, soup and onion.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix cereal and margarine and top casserole.
Bake until browned.

title: graham cracker roll
directions: Mix 2 egg yolks in one cup Sego milk and stir over heat until the mixture coats a spoon (do not let boil).

Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons butter and cool slightly while you mix 3/4 cup of sugar (if you don't like it too sweet, use 2/3 cup sugar), 1 small 9 ounce can of crushed pineapple and 1 teaspoon vanilla and add the milk mixture, then beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Count 36 graham crackers.
Crush 12 and sprinkle into pan.
Spread 1/2 of mixture gently over them, then sprinkle 12 more crackers, rest of the mixture and sprinkle remaining crackers over top. Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook oleo, sugar, egg yolks and dates over low heat 10 minutes.
When cool enough to handle, mix nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla into cooked mixture, then roll in small balls; roll in coconut.

title: empadas
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add one egg yolk, mixing well until mixture resembles coarse oatmeal.
Add margarine and shortening and mix until dough becomes soft.
Do not overmix, but just until it holds together with fingertips.
Press small portions of dough into cupcake tins.

title: rhubarb upside down cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into bottom of a large pan.
Prepare a yellow or white cake mix and pour into pan over the mixture.
Next mix the rest of the ingredients.
Put this on top yet and bake at 350° for 1 hour. When cooled, drizzle with icing.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Break into pieces.
Cut up cauliflower and lettuce.
Add cheese, mayo and sugar.
Stir together.
Add lettuce last.

title: baked beans
directions: Dice bacon; fry until about half done.
Add chopped onion. When onion is slightly done, pour off fat.
Add pork and beans, sugar and catsup; stir well.
Cover; cook on low heat for 30 minutes, or bake in oven.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soup, onion, water and rice mix.
Put chicken on top; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease and flour 10 x 13-inch jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with solid grease, not Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add sugar and pumpkin.
Mix together remaining ingredients, then add to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Bake 17 minutes.
Immediately flip onto linen (not terrycloth) towel that you have covered with powdered sugar. Roll up and let sit for 1/2 hour.

title: curried seafood delight
directions: In large bowl, mix crab meat, tuna, eggs and apple.
Melt butter in skillet, add green pepper and onions; saute.
Stir in curry and flour until well blended.
Slowly add half and half and cook until mixture thickens.
Pour over crab meat mixture, blend well.
Pour into baking dish, sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Drain the Ricotta or cottage cheese.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Divide stuffing into 12 parts.
Place a mound of stuffing on each cooked noodle.
Spread a thin layer of the meat sauce on the bottom of a baking dish.
Arrange sauce over the top.
Sprinkle a teaspoon of Parmesan cheese over each of the manicotti.
Bake in a preheated oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken-rice divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Arrange broccoli in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle with half the Parmesan cheese; top with chicken or turkey.
Season meat with salt and pepper; spoon rice over.
Melt the butter or margarine; blend in flour.
Add milk, all at once; cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice; fold in sour cream.
Pour sauce evenly over chicken; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tammy's hot dog sauce
directions: Brown onions in pan with a little vegetable oil.
Add hamburg; brown.
When brown, add spices and 2 quarts water. Simmer for 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Can be frozen or canned. Yields a lot!

title: fruit punch(sugarless)
directions: Mix diet white soda and pineapple juice together.
Mix diet Kool-Aid powder and water.
Stir well; add to soda and juice mixture.
Add ice.
Kids love this.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: brownie supreme
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients until blended.
Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Spread batter in prepared 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (well-greased).
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until they pull from side of pan.
Heat chocolate topping and pour over brownies.
After cutting, spoon ice cream onto brownies and sprinkle with cocoa.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Cut up celery and carrots. Mix together soups and water; add salt and pepper.
Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and eggs.
Add peanut butter and beat well.
Mix flour, soda and salt together.
Add vanilla.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: lime pear jello salad
directions: Drain pears and heat juice.
Mash pears.
Add Jell-O to heated juice.
Dissolve thoroughly.
Add mashed pears to Jell-O mixture. Chill until slightly set.
Whip cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Whip the whipping cream.
Fold into Jell-O mixture.
Put in mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: fudgy brownie
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup vegetable oil.
Add boiling water.
Stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup vegetable oil. Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend completely. Stir in peanut butter.

title: kris' kwik chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine broth and water in medium saucepan.
Add celery, onion and carrot.
Add chicken and broth.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles to boiling broth.
Cook until done, about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce at least 4 hours. Drain.
Dip each water chestnut in sugar then wrap in half strips of bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes, turning after 10 minutes.

title: citrus slush
directions: Bring sugar and 3 cups water to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add frozen juices and stir until melted.
Add pineapple juice and other 3 cups of water.
Mix well.

title: celebration frost
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sherbet and ginger ale.
Add just before serving.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and shortening until crumbly (like pie crust mixture) and reserve 1/2 cup crumbs for topping.

title: tile cleaner
directions: Mix and use to clean tile.
Rub lemon oil on the tile afterward.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in shallow 3-quart baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown meat in heavy ovenproof pot.
Place in preheated 300° oven, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add onion, slightly browned, to pork chops before cooking.

title: triple orange delight
directions: Drain mandarin oranges; save juice.
Bring 1 cup of juice to a boil.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Pour into large bowl. Add sherbet.
Stir in until melted.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Using a 13 x 9-inch pan, tear 1/2 of your angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Cut 1/2 of your mandarin oranges over top of angel food cake.
Place 1/2 of mixture over top of cake and oranges.
Repeat until you use all your ingredients.
Garnish with Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.

title: chili
directions: Brown onions, garlic powder and meat in oil.
When brown, add everything else except tomato paste and beans.
When chili is almost done, which will be about 2 to 3 hours, add tomato paste and beans.
Let cook until done.

title: spicy cherry sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine about half of the sugar, the cornstarch and a dash of salt; stir in orange juice and lemon juice.
Stir in undrained cherries, cinnamon and cloves.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in remaining sugar.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Serve warm with ham or pork.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach, discard stems and tear into a salad bowl.
Add sliced onions and chill several hours.
Combine other ingredients, except bacon and egg.
Pour over sliced mushrooms and chill.
When ready to serve, add dressing to spinach and toss.
Sprinkle with egg and bacon.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef in water until tender.
Combine butter and flour in saucepan.
Add water gradually cooking until slightly thickened. Simmer all vegetables and salt and pepper for about 20 minutes. Combine all ingredients together and simmer for 10 more minutes on low heat.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: five spice jerk chicken
directions: In a skillet cook onion and garlic in olive oil for 5 minutes.
Add habanero pepper; cook until lightly browned.
Add jerk seasoning, salt, mango juice, orange juice and red wine vinegar.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Place chicken in a bowl and coat with mixture; marinate for 1 hour.
Remove from marinade.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together until well blended; add eggs.
Stir in chopped walnuts and well mashed bananas. Add flour, soda and salt mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Combine sugars, margarine, oil, egg, and vanilla; beat till creamy. Combine flour, salt, soda, and cream of tartar. Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Stir in cornflakes, coconut, oats, and pecans. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown
onion,
pepper
and
beef
in saucepan on top of stove. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer covered 1 hour, adding beans last 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan soup
directions: Peel eggplant, if desired.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: not too sweet pecan pie
directions: Cream butter to soften.
Add sugar.
Beat until creamy and fluffy.
Add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in a 9-inch pie shell at 350° for 50 minutes or until a toothpick is clean.

title: roast beef
directions: Brown stew meat in cooking oil.
Drain grease.
Add mushroom gravy, tomato juice, soup mix, and water.
Cover and let simmer about 15 minutes.
Put potatoes in a casserole dish and cover with meat mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is well cooked.
Stir once or twice during cooking.

title: taffy
directions: First volunteer four kinds of peas:

title: venison jerky
directions: Note:
You can use any seasons that you like.

title: chicken salad with potato sticks
directions: Mix well at least 24 hours before serving.
Fourty-eight hours is even better.
Cover tightly and do not disturb.
Place in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, mix 1 large can shoestring potato sticks into salad.
This gives it "crunch".

title: mexican salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for several hours. Amount of chopped vegetables may be modified to suit taste.

title: fresh peach custard pie
directions: Place peaches in pastry shell.
Combine sugar, salt, and flour with eggs.
Stir in cream.
Pour over peaches.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: tea syrup
directions: Bring the gallon of water to a boil in a large pot. Add tea bags to boiling water and turn off heat. Let tea stand for 15 minutes. Add the sugar to the mixture. Stir. (This will make your tea syrup.) Mix 3 1/2 cups of syrup with a gallon of water. This recipe will make about 6 gallons of tea.

title: onion cheese dip for vegies
directions: Combine in small bowl and chill!

title: brownies
directions: Bake in greased pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix vegetable oil and eggs.
Add salt, soda, cinnamon, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Fold in cups of finely, diced apples and nuts if desired.
Batter will be thick, not runny.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (300° for electric oven).

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
In bacon drippings, saute onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Add rice and fry about 5 minutes.
Add pimentos.
Reduce heat to warm.
Add shrimp and crumbled bacon.
Stir in soy sauce until brown.
Serve.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Let each person prepare his/her own dish by beginning with rice, then chili, lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese with crumbled chips on top and taco sauce over all.

title: pie crust (for 1 pie)
directions: Sift flour and salt; add sugar.
Work quickly, with the tips of the fingers, the shortening into the mixture.
Use enough cold water to make the particles of the mixture stick together.
Turn on floured pastry board and roll, handling as little as possible.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and shortening together very well.
Add molasses, ginger, beaten eggs and salt.
Sift soda with the first 2 cups of flour; add to mixture.
Add hot water and cinnamon; stir well.
Mix in remaining flour, 2 cups at a time.
Let stand overnight.
Batter can be shaped nicely while cold.
Place cookies on greased cookie sheet; sprinkle with granulated or confectioners sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven until done, 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully; ovens vary.

title: rainbow fruit salad
directions: In a glass serving dish or bowl, mix orange juice, lime juice and sugar.
Add grapes, kiwi, blueberries, oranges and banana; stir gently.
Sprinkle red berries over top of fruit, cover bowl and refrigerate.
(Fruit may be mixed the day before serving.)

title: seven up cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and lemon extract.
Fold in Seven-Up.
Pour into well greased 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add cake mix to yeast mixture.
Let stand a few minutes after mixing.
Then add flour; mix well and let rise until doubled.
Cover mixture.
Punch down and roll out half of dough at a time to a little over 1/4-inch thick on a floured surface.
Spread melted butter and sprinkle cinnamon and sugar to desired amount.
Roll up and slice long roll in 1 1/2-inch slices. Place on Pam sprayed pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° until golden brown or 25 to 30 minutes.

title: maple syrup cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs, maple flavoring, butter and maple syrup. Mix together dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture. Stir in the boiling water and nuts. Chill for 1 hour, then drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15-16 minutes.

title: baked pineapple pudding
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat the eggs and add to creamed
mixture.
Cube the toast and add to mixture along with the
can of pineapple.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: banana cream pie(weight watchers pie)
directions: Melt peanut butter and honey together.
Add Rice Krispies and mix together to make pie crust; pat mixture in pie pan.
Make pudding (mix for only one minute).
Slice bananas onto crust. Pour pudding into crust.
Add bananas on to the top for decoration.
Chill.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add both brown and regular sugar, beating well.
Next, add eggs, peanut butter, vanilla and corn syrup.
Beat well.
Add oats, soda and salt; mix.
Finally, stir in all remaining ingredients.

title: nina's really good chicken casserole
directions: Mix together crackers and margarine. Press most of cracker mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 baking pan. Add chicken, then mix together sour cream and soup and pour on top of chicken. Sprinkle remaining cracker mixture on top of soups and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick pasta and veggies
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Add salt, oil and pasta; mix well.
Return to boil.
Add veggies on top.
Don't mix; return to boil.
Put on lid.
Turn off the heat for 10 minutes.
Take off stove.
Drain in colander.
Place on platter and serve!

title: newcomers' club of the lake area
directions: Mix all ingredients and you have the Newcomers' Club of the Lake Area.

title: steak sauce
directions: Combine ingredients together and heat in saucepan until butter is melted.
Brush steak or spoon mixture over meat while on grill or in the oven.
Very good!

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix well and shape into balls.
Melt chocolate chips with paraffin in the top of a double boiler.
Keep hot and dip balls. Put on wax paper to dry.
Makes approximately 50.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Disjoint chicken wings, cut off tips.
Set wings aside.
Mix all other ingredients in pan.
Heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over chicken wings and marinate for 12 hours. Refrigerate while marinating.
Stir occasionally to coat.
Bake in oven uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir once or twice while baking.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Stir in milk slowly.
Add butter and cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Count time when rolling boil starts.
Have large bowl ready with oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour hot mix over oat mix and stir well.
Drop on waxed paper.
One cup of ground peanuts may be used instead of peanut butter.

title: pizza pie
directions: Put in pie crust in layers of Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Mix meat with sauce and paste; lay atop cheese.
Add remaining cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream the butter, salt and sugar; add the egg and milk.
Work in lightly flour and baking powder sifted together.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thickness on towel or floured board.
Cut with a doughnut cutter and fry in Crisco or oil.
Doughnuts should come quickly to the surface of the fat.
When browned on one side, turn them over on the other side.
Drain on unglazed paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: oreo delight
directions: You will need a 9 x 11-inch glass pan.
Crumble cookies and melted margarine together.
Put half of mixture in bottom of pan. Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Pour on top of cookies.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Pour on top of Cool Whip mixture.
Add rest of cookies on top.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: old-fashioned shoo-fly pie(makes 2 pies; serves 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together flour, butter and sugar. Reserve 1 1/2 cups for crumbs.
In another bowl, mix together molasses, eggs, water and baking soda.
Add to flour mixture (not the reserved crumbs).
Pour into two ungreased 9-inch pie plates. Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add cream of chicken soup and green chiles; stir.
Add deboned chicken; season.
Line glass baking dish with slightly broken chips.
Pour chicken mixture over the Doritos.
Top with thin layer of broken Doritos and cheese; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk, add sugar and mix well.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening together.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture; stir to mix.
This is real sticky to start with so knead on well floured board by working more flour into dough until it is of rolling consistency.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut in desired shape.
Dip in melted butter.
Stack 2 biscuits together. Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
Stir together spinach, sour cream, soup mix, salad dressing or mayonnaise, chopped chestnuts, green onions and seafood.
Blend well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Put hot water only in Jell-O and mix well. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Put in refrigerator until it is jelled.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: fat hen dumplings
directions: Remove chicken from broth when tender.
Combine broth, salt and baking powder.
Add enough flour to make a dough stiff enough to roll out, but not too stiff.
Roll out very thin.
Cut into pieces and drop into boiling broth.
Reduce heat until just boiling and place lid on cooker and cook until done.

title: broccoli -n- cheese quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: date bars
directions: Sift the flour with the baking powder.
Beat the eggs, then add the sugar. Add the vanilla and salt.
Mix in the sifted flour and powder along with the dates and nuts. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Careful, they dry out quickly.
Powder with confectioners sugar.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain the peas, beans and hominy.
Mix well in large bowl. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: fancy oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients except dry soup mix.
Place in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Bake, stirring occasionally in 300° oven for 3 hours or 350° oven for 2 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: sesame-ginger chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients in small bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Place chicken between 2 sheets waxed paper and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place chicken in mixture and then on grill.
Baste while grilling.
Cook approximately 4 minutes on each side.

title: old-fashioned potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until soft and drain.
Add milk and beat thoroughly; season to taste.
Work butter into flour; add egg and milk.
Drop by teaspoon into hot milk.
Cover saucepan and cook about 10 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding (use 3 cups milk) and stir in Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish with graham crackers.
Pour some of pudding mixture over crackers.
Make another layer of graham crackers and pour on remainder of
pudding.
Make another layer of graham crackers.
Ice the top layer of crackers with the chocolate icing.
Refrigerate and serve the next day.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: grandma's strawberry custard
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix.
Place berries, sliced, in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle sugar over berries; pour mixture over berries. Break margarine in small pieces and put on top of pie; bake at 325° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients. Form small balls. Bake 15 to 30 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet until golden brown. Makes about 6 dozen. Can be frozen uncooked.

title: cheese straws
directions: Note:
May use medium or sharp cheese if wish.

title: thimbleberry jam
directions: Wash and grind berries until crushed completely.
Pour sugar into a dry dish.
Measure 6 cups of berries into a large kettle. Add pectin and stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Add measured sugar and mix well.
Continue stirring and bring to a full rolling boil. Boil jam exactly 5 minutes.
Pour into prepared jars and seal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add chopped ham, parsley, mustard and Tabasco sauce.
Cover and keep refrigerated for 5 hours.
Form into ball and roll in peanuts.

title: catfish court bouillon
directions: Place onions (about 1/2) in bottom of pot that has been sprayed with nonstick product.
Layer fish, tomato sauce, bell pepper and celery until all ingredients are used.
Pour Ro-Tel last, topping with green onions and parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Shake pot; do not stir.
Serve over rice.

title: wine drop cookies
directions: Dissolve soda into cold coffee.
Cream ingredients together. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: honey french chicken
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients.
Place chicken in casserole dish and pour mixture evenly over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: simple carrot cake
directions: Mix the sugar, oil, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Then mix in flour and eggs.
Fold or mix in carrots.
Bake at 350°F for 1 hour.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 2-quart casserole. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening. Add sugar.
Beat eggs and add.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make sure to add the milk before the flour. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 325°, then bake 30 minutes longer.

title: rumacky
directions: Cut water chestnuts in thirds.
Cut bacon strips in thirds. Wrap water chestnuts or pineapple chunks with bacon and put toothpick through to hold.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until done.
Drain off grease and place rolls in small casserole. Sprinkle enough brown sugar to cover and pour catsup over all. Bake at 350° until it bubbles, 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook
potatoes and onion in salt water until well done. Without
draining
water, mash potatoes with hand masher until water is thickened.
Add crumbled bacon and minced clams.
Add half and half and season to taste and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Serve
immediately.	Makes
approximately
to
1 1/2 gallons depending on potato broth.

title: date apple cookies
directions: Heat dates and water and mash, no need if using raisins.
Mix all together.
Let sit until ingredients stick together.
Drop on sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: deer bologna
directions: Mix the ingredients until very well blended.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Stuff
and	bake 4 hours at 200°, turning every 1/2 hour. I make bags out of white material approximately 3 x 14-inches. Will make 4 or 5.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Salt and pepper the potatoes to taste and pour Italian dressing over potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon and blend together.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Just before serving, crumble the bacon on top.
Serves 10.

title: new england steamed chocolate pudding
directions: Cream shortening, soda, vanilla and sugar well.
Add chocolate and blend.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Pour into a 1-quart mold which has been greased.
Cover with waxed paper and secure with a rubber band.
Steam for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with Sunshine Sauce.

title: apricot-pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Bring juice, water and sugar to a boil. Remove from heat and add gelatin and cream cheese.
Beat with mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Cool.
Add pineapple, pecans and celery.
Chill until it begins to set like jelly.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Chill until set.

title: tennis brunch casserole
directions: Crumble
sausage in a medium skillet.
Cook over medium heat until
brown,
stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Line bottom of a
buttered baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforations
to
seal.
Sprinkle
with
sausage and cheese. Combine
remaining
ingredients;
beat
well and pour over sausage.
Bake
at 425° for 15 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour the can of peaches into an 8 x 8 oven dish.
Evenly sprinkle the cake mix over peaches.
Cut the butter into long thin slices and place all over the dry batter.
Bake at 350° until the top is golden brown.

title: fried rice
directions: In a large pan or wok; fry onions and celery in oil until soft.
Fry pork strips.
Add cold rice and shrimp.
Stir until hot.
Season with salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Make a light omelet with the eggs (I use Egg Beaters); roll and slice in thin strips. Place rice mixture on a platter or in a large bowl.
Garnish with omelet strips, green onions, raisins, nuts and strips of lettuce. Serve hot, using more soy sauce if desired.

title: baked chicken in sauce
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Pour over cut up chicken pieces. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken cacciatore(to be served over medium-size spaghetti)
directions: Heat oil; add pepper, onion, garlic and mushrooms and saute until tender.
Remove vegetables and saute chicken strips until they are tender and begin to brown.
Add the wine and broth, tomatoes and spices.
Simmer until thick.
Serve over pasta.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Bone chicken after cooking.
Cut into small chunks and spread into oblong baking dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion and pepper. Pour over chicken.
Crumble the saltine crackers and spread over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves six.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Blend flour, salt, soda and spices.
Set aside. Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, molasses.
Blend in flour mixture. Refrigerate one hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in small amount of sugar.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container when cool.

title: gnocchis
directions: Mix together all ingredients to make dough.
Pull off handfuls of dough and roll between your hands to make long log, 1/2 inch in diameter.
Cut log into 1/2-inch strips and roll them over a grater.
Place on cookie sheet, laying in a single layer, and put in freezer for several hours, until they are frozen.
Boil water in large pot.
Put in gnocchis; allow gnocchis to rise.
Cook approximately 10 minutes more.
Serve with spaghetti sauce and meatballs.

title: coconut cake
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Grease and flour cake pan. Follow directions for cake on box.
Bake.
When done, fill cake with holes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Roll each piece in mixture of white sugar and cinnamon.
Drop in greased Bundt pan or angel food pan. Melt butter and add brown sugar; pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan at once.
Pull off and eat like a monkey!

title: quick and easy pork chops
directions: Put rice on bottom of pan, then pork chops and soup mix. Cover well with water.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix well and chill at least two hours all ingredients, except French bread and Mozzarella cheese.
Slice French bread 1-inch thick.
Spread meat on bread and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 415° for 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and nutmeg. Mix thoroughly.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water as directed on package.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients together, except for 3 egg whites.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Pour into cooked pie crust. Beat and top with the 3 egg whites.
Brown.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: The night before serving, mix all of the ingredients except paprika.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Just before serving, sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: lemon crumb dessert
directions: Have ready 4 cups vanilla wafer or graham cracker crumbs. Dissolve gelatin, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add lemon rind and juice.
Chill until very thick.
Add evaporated milk and whip until fluffy.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Make 3 wells in dry ingredients. In one well put vanilla, in another well put vinegar and in the last well put oil.
Pour 1 cup of cold water over all and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Then turn to 300° for 50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat, drain. Add onion, bell pepper and celery, cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients, mix well. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membrane. Precook pepper cups in boiling salted water about 5 minutes. Drain; sprinkle inside with salt.
Brown meat and onion in hot shortening.
Add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until rice is almost tender (5 minutes).
Add cheese; stuff peppers and stand upright in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven for 25 minutes, until hot.
Sprinkle with more cheese.

title: one dish meal
directions: Mix onion, celery, rice, carrots and soyameat in large bowl. Put oil, soup, water and broth into saucepan; heat and stir until smooth.
Pour sauce over casserole and mix gently.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hunting camp slaw
directions: Mix ingredients; refrigerate in covered container.
Keeps for weeks.

title: marinated black-eyed pea salad
directions: Drain peas and add all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: devils food cake with soft chocolate icing
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening then add eggs and vanilla and stir well.
Then add flour, cocoa, soda, salt, and buttermilk and boiling water.
Bake in sheet pan 350 degrees until done.

title: he-man casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Add salt and pepper, green pepper, noodles, tomato soup and corn.
Mix well and pour into shallow casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream-noodle bake
directions: Saute ground steak in butter in skillet until brown.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: polish cabbage in sour cream
directions: Cut cabbage finely.
Melt butter in large skillet and saute cabbage until tender, but not brown, about 15 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix together egg, sour cream, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over cooked cabbage.
Toss lightly and heat through, but do not boil.
Serves 4.

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider and cinnamon stick in large pan.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer uncovered 5 minutes more.
Keep hot until ready to serve. Yields 20 cups.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water and add fruit; let jell.
Mix sugar, sour cream and cream cheese. Spread on top of Jell-O mixture.
Top with chopped pecans.

title: bittersweet chocolate sauce
directions: In a heavy, medium saucepan melt chocolate and margarine or butter over low heat until melted, stirring frequently.
Add milk, sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a gentle boil over medium heat. Boil gently, stirring frequently for 8 minutes or until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm.
To store, cover tightly and refrigerate for up to 1 week.
Makes 1 cup.

title: hattie's texas style corn and tomatoes
directions: Cook onion in fat until transparent.
Do not brown.
Add sugar, tomatoes and corn.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 20 to 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Use iron skillet.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Combine and beat first 4 ingredients. Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of paper cup cake paper. (If using miniature cups, break wafers up, and use enough to cover bottom.)
Fill about 2/3 full. Bake 15 minutes at 350 degrees. Top with favorite fruit pie filling. Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake at 425° for five minutes.
Then turn oven to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let set a while before serving.
Top with ice cream.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir in stuffing mix.
Line bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan.
Save enough chunks to sprinkle over top.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and cherries, reserving only 1/2 cup syrup from peaches.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions. Fold cherries, peaches and the reserved peach syrup into the Dream Whip.

Add halved maraschino cherries and marshmallows and freeze. Keep frozen until approximately 45 minutes before serving time. (This can be dished up and frozen in cupcake cups, then frozen, then remove only what you need to serve.)

title: cracky bars
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt. Blend together Crisco and sugar, creaming well. Add well beaten eggs. Combine milk and vanilla. Add this creamed mixture to the sifted dry ingredients. Place 1/3 of the batter in a second bowl.
Add 1 square melted chocolate and walnuts.
Spread in a well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Arrange graham crackers over batter in pan.
Add chocolate chips to remaining 2/3 batter. Drop by spoonful over crackers and spread to cover. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut in squares when cooled.

title: cinnamon chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in eggs.
Blend well.
Add sour cream and beat until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat slightly.
(Batter will be very thick.)
Spread 1/2 batter into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cinnamon-sugar mixture over batter.
Put 1/2 chips over that.
Spread remaining batter on top and repeat cinnamon and chip layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Boil 1/2, cut side down, for 20 minutes.
Scoop out the squash.
Mix and place in shell of squash the cooked squash, cheese, grated zucchini, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic powder and basil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 days before using.

title: cranberry christmas punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in frozen concentrate. Place in a punch bowl two trays of ice cubes or a molded ice ring (molded ring is good made with cranberry juice).
Pour punch over ice.
Slowly pour in chilled ginger ale.
Fruit flavored sherbet may be added if desired.

title: caesar salad
directions: Sprinkle bowl with garlic salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Layer lettuce, oranges, croutons and mushrooms.
Sprinkle more garlic salt, cheese and pepper.
Add another layer of lettuce, mushrooms, oranges and croutons.

title: popcorn crackles
directions: Melt butter.
