Add sugar, salt and molasses.
Boil to the hard crack stage.
Pour over corn; stir while pouring.
Spread in thin layer to cool.
Break in pieces.

title: strawberry salad mold
directions: First, combine jello with boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Second, fold in all at once the thawed strawberries with the juice, the well drained pineapple, the bananas and walnuts.
Third, turn half of mixture into dish.
When firm, spread with sour cream, using the whole pint.
Then add the other half of the fruit jello mixture, that has been slightly thickened. Set until firm.
Serve on lettuce.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: root vegetables with chicken(popular and good)
directions: Pare sato-imo thinly.
Rub with salt and rinse well in water to remove slime from surface.
Cut all ingredients into bite size pieces.
Soak lotus root and burdock root in water immediately to keep from discoloring.
Boil konnyaku lightly.

title: extra thick shake
directions: Place in a blender and blend until smooth.

title: carrie's spinach and cheese calzone
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well (very important).
Squeeze spinach to remove excess water.
In skillet, cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add spinach; heat through. In mixing bowl, combine half of beaten egg, Ricotta, Parmesan and spinach mixture.
Divide pizza dough in half.
On cookie sheet lined with foil, flatten dough into 2 circles.
Don't get too thin!
Fill each with half of the spinach-cheese mixture.
Pull dough up and over mixture, forming a semi-circle, and pinch well to close.
Brush with remaining beaten egg.
Bake for 14 minutes. Serve with your favorite marinara sauce.
Makes 2 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch casserole, layer meat and seasoning. Sprinkle onion and cheese over. Put in vegetables, then cover with mushroom soup and top with Tater Tots or hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: honey dijon dressing
directions: Mix and store in the refrigerator.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter pan.
Slice apples in pan. Combine dry ingredients. Add egg and mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon over mix. Drip butter over all. Bake at 375° until apples are done and crumb topping is golden brown.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Mix together flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Blend together egg, milk and shortening or oil.
Add liquid all at once to flour mixture until flour is moistened.
(Batter may be lumpy.)
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cupful batter onto preheated skillet or griddle.
Immediately place desired amount of chocolate chips on the pancakes.
Bake until small bubbles appear, then turn and bake until golden brown.
Serve topped with butter or margarine and your favorite syrup.
Makes 16 to 18 pancakes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Mix all ingredients cold and cook over boiling water 1 hour, stirring often. Strain. Flavor with vanilla.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Set aside. Beat eggs with sugar 2 minutes.
Add oil and beat.
Add lemon juice.
Alternately fold in dry ingredients.
Stir in zucchini. Then pecans and raisins.
Do not overmix.

title: fresh german apple cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs until smooth. Add flour and cinnamon. Stir in pecans.
Bake in metal baking pan.
Place butterscotch morsels on top of mixture. Bake at 300° to 325° until golden brown.

title: banquet spaghetti supper
directions: Fry peppers, onions and garlic in oil until done, adding a little water to keep it soft.
Mash with a fork.
Add beef; cook until done.
Place mixture in a large pot; add all remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Prepare spaghetti as directed. Add a small amount of olive oil.
Drain.
Combine sauce and spaghetti in pot or serve sauce over spaghetti on plate.
Makes 152 servings.

title: beef pot roast in a barbecue sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle the onions over the bottom of a large, heavy pot or Dutch oven.
Place the meat on top of the onions.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours, adding some stock if the pan juices begin to dry up.

title: brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 7 x 11-inch greased pan; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: food processor pie crust
directions: Position knife blade in processor bowl; add flour and salt. Top with cover and process, pulsing 3 to 4 times or until combined. Add shortening to flour mixture; process 5 to 6 short pulses until mixture resembles coarse meal.
With processor running, slowly add water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until dough forms a ball. Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Roll as usual. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields pastry for one 9-inch pie.

title: easy cheesy chicken
directions: Put a little chicken and cheese in each roll and roll it up. Lay them in a casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and rolls are slightly browned on the top.

title: chicken international
directions: Cook chicken and debone it.
Cut into pieces.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and salt, stirring constantly for 3 minutes.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are almost soft.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: no bake strawberry cheese cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese with the powdered sugar.
Whip the package of Dream Whip with milk and vanilla according to package instructions. Fold the cream cheese with the Dream Whip.
Pour the cheese mixture into the graham cracker crust.
Put the cooled strawberry mixture on top.
Put the pan into the refrigerator for a couple of hours or more to harden.

title: zina's southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in the nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: "tastes like olive garden soup"
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer together 20 minutes.
Serve hot with cornbread or bread sticks.
Delicious.

title: chocolate frosties
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: brown sugar pecans
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients, adding pecans last.
Drop by teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Combine. Unroll cake and frost with mixture.
Roll cake again (without towel) and chill.

title: supreme banana bread
directions: Mix baking soda and sour cream by hand and set aside.
Mix sugar, margarine and eggs until sugar is absorbed.
Mash bananas and vanilla and add to creamed mixture.
Slowly add flour and salt. Add pecans.
Add sour cream mixture; mix well and pour into greased loaf pan.
You can put in small foil pans (3 small).
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 335°.
Makes 3 mini loaves.

title: low-fat raisin nut bran muffins
directions: Mix.
Grease top and cover with wax paper and let rise all day or night.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Heat chicken broth and hash browns until potatoes get mushy. Add cream of potato soup.
Add pieces of cheese.
Keep stirring so it won't stick.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Pour melted margarine over sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: 10 bean soup
directions: Soak washed beans in 2 quarts water for 10 to 12 hours.
Add ham bone and cook 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot chocolate milk
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 2/3 cup hot water.

title: fruit slush
directions: In a blender container, place fruit.
In proportion of 2 parts ice to 1 part fruit, add ice cubes 2 at a time, processing constantly.
Into glass, pour fruit mixture.
Add enough club soda to make desired consistency.
Garnish with kiwi fruit slices or fresh mint.

title: josie's brunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with a nonstick spray.

title: dreamy macaroni entree
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; add cottage cheese, sour cream, Velveeta cheese, Cheddar cheese and 1 egg.
Mix and put into casserole.
Sprinkle Durkee crispy French fried onions on top. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Combine ingredients until blended.
Add crabmeat and mix well. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk, stir in crumbs, onions, parsley, salt and 1/8 tsp pepper.
Add beef and mix well.
Pat in a ring in a shallow pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat.
Combine catsup, sugar and mustard; spread over meat. Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In small plastic bag, combine flour and red pepper; coat chicken.
Bake 20 minutes.
Mix butter, hot pepper sauce and barbecue sauce with orange juice.
Pour half of mixture over chicken.
Broil 10 minutes.
Turn chicken; pour rest of sauce on.
Broil again until crisp.

title: apple breakfast pie
directions: Combine Bisquick, egg, milk, 1/2 cup sugar, oil, nuts and raisins.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pan.
Top with apples. Combine 2 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and butter; sprinkle on top. Bake at 375° until done.

title: one dish chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Mix stuffing, water and margarine lightly.
Spoon stuffing across center of 2-quart shallow baking dish, leaving space on both sides for chicken.
Place chicken on each side.
Mix soup, milk and parsley; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 400° for 15 minutes; uncover and bake 15 minutes more or until chicken is done.

title: burt's favorite frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Beat with electric beater for 4 to 6 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: london broil
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place meat in a large baking dish and pour the mixture over meat.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 4 hours, turning the meat occasionally.
Remove the meat from marinade and drain well.
Heat a large skillet over moderately high heat (375°).
Sprinkle pan with a small amount of salt and brown meat 5 to 6 minutes on each side.
Reduce heat to medium low (225°).
Cook ten minutes or to the degree of desired doneness.
Cut diagonal slices across grain.
This is a family favorite!

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add well beaten eggs and salt, also soda dissolved in hot water.
Add flour and sour milk alternately, then orange juice, rind, raisins and coconut.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes in layers.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put all in jar with lid. Shake well.

title: pig lickin' cake
directions: Mix in blender eggs, oil, and oranges.
Add to the dry cake mix.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a lightly greased 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Mix juice saved from the pineapple and dry pudding together.
Fold in the Cool Whip and pineapple.
Spread over cooled cake as a topping.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Beat sugar, oil and eggs with mixture.
Do not use mixer for rest of cake.
Add spices and flour; mix well.
Add apples and nuts; mix well.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Mix together well and chill in refrigerator.

title: stuffed angel food cake
directions: Cut cake in half; scoop out inside of one cake half.
Mix strawberries and Cool Whip with cake crumbs scooped from cake half.
Fill scooped half with this mixture.
Place cake halves together.
Ice cake with Cool Whip and serve chilled.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: potato apple skillet
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper over potatoes. Heat oil in skillet. Place potatoes, apples, onion, and celery in hot oil. Cook, covered for 20 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with cheese. Serve hot.

title: mexican noodle casserole
directions: Cook hamburger; drain grease.
Add beef flavor packets from the Oodles of Noodles to the hamburger; mix thoroughly.
Add taco sauce to hamburger mixture.
Cook over medium heat until warm. Add hot sauce to taste.
Cook noodles; drain.
Place noodles on serving platter; top with the hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with sour cream; serve with tortilla chips.

title: crock pot wassail
directions: Pour apple juice, cranberry juice, sugar, bitters, cinnamon and allspice into Crock Pot. Stud orange with cloves.
Add to juice mixture. Add rum.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Simmer on Low for 4 to 8 hours.
Serve warm.
Yield: 12 cups.

title: ruby's cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine flour, cream of tartar and salt; set aside.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and Crisco together, then beat in eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand until raised with foam on top.
Mix together yeast mixture, sugar mixture, milk and vanilla. Add 4 cups flour mixture and mix well.
Add 2 cups more flour mixture and mix well. Add remaining flour mixture and mix well again. Turn out onto a floured
board and knead for 15 minutes.
Put into a large bowl and cover.
Set bowl in a warm place until mixture has doubled in size.
When double, work down, cover and let sit until double in size again.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: In large skillet, heat margarine until melted.
Spread sauerkraut evenly over margarine in skillet.
Sprinkle with rice, then onion.
Top with ground chuck, salt, pepper and tomato sauce. Cover skillet, cook over low heat 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: pakistani chicken
directions: Pour over chicken, cover and refrigerate at least one hour (even better if marinated overnight).
Barbecue chicken on outdoor grill.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Spread all the ingredients except lemon juice and cranberry sauce
as bottom layer in a regular size loaf pan (wet, shake out and line with aluminum foil).
Spread lemon juice and cranberry sauce over cream cheese mix.
Freeze and slice.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Drain sweet potatoes. Mash them in mixing bowl.
Add 1 egg, 1 cup white sugar and 1 stick melted butter or margarine. Mix together.
Put into baking dish.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: In a large bowl, mix together cucumbers, onions, green bell peppers, garlic, and salt.
Allow to stand approximately three hours.
In a large saucepan, mix the cider vinegar, white sugar, mustard seed, celery seed, whole cloves, and turmeric. Bring to a boil.
Drain liquid from the cucumber mixture.
Stir the mixture into the boiling vinegar mixture.
Remove from heat shortly before the combined mixtures return to boil. Transfer to sterile containers.
Seal and chill in the refrigerator until serving.

title: sour cream twists
directions: Place sour cream in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in 2 tablespoons oleo, 3 tablespoons sugar, baking soda and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in beaten egg and yeast.
Stir to dissolve. Using a spoon; add flour gradually.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly to form smooth dough.
Let stand 5 minutes. Roll out to form a 6 x 24-inch rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick. Spread entire surface with 2 tablespoons softened oleo.
Sprinkle 1/2 rectangle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cover with unsugared half.
Cut in 24 (1-inch) strips.
Twist and let rise.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: spring breeze cheese cake(strawberry)
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust. Chill 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: one step karidopeta(nut cake)
directions: You get better results when the cake ingredients are all at room temperature that are ordinarily cold.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all your dry ingredients together first. Add eggs and blend well. Add sugar, water, oil and pumpkin. Once this is mixed well, add pecans. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: salad-toss
directions: Tear romaine and endive.
Slice radishes and onions and combine rest of ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for several hours to crisp.
Serve with dressing.

title: percolator punch
directions: In basket of percolator put brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
In bottom of percolator put cranberry juice, apple juice and pineapple juice.
Use a large, such as 33 cup percolator.
Use a filter in top if you like to keep particles out of punch.
Let the percolator run regular perk cycle.
This is "the best" hot punch.
Makes 25 to 30 cups.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken 1/2 hour; debone.
Steam broccoli until tender. Heat soup; add mayo, salt and lemon juice.
Heat through.
Add cheese until blended.
In casserole drain and add broccoli.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Spread sauce over top.
Place bread crumbs tossed with melted butter on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cheese pie
directions: Spread butter evenly over bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan. Press 1 1/3 cups of the coconut into butter, forming a shell. Place 1 cup of the coconut, eggs, sugar, cheese and lemon juice in blender or processor.
Blend until smooth, about 1 1/2 minutes. Pour into coconut shell.
Sprinkle remaining coconut in a ring around top and center.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
If coconut browns quickly, cover with a circle of aluminum foil.

title: grandma jacobsens icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Roll into two rolls, wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
Slice thin and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° on an ungreased sheet.
They get better after a while.
Last weeks.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Divide into 2 or 3 balls.
Shape on plate.
Chill. Roll in nuts, if desired.

title: wassail
directions: Combine in a large pan or wok.
Heat and simmer 5 minutes. Serve hot.

title: coating mix for oven fried chicken
directions: Blend together ingredients with fork or pastry blender; mix well.
Store in airtight container until ready to use.
(Not necessary to refrigerate.)

title: night before brunch bake
directions: Great for Christmas breakfast.

title: peanut butter cookie pops
directions: You will need 10 wooden sticks.

title: soda scones
directions: Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar into a large bowl.
Work in butter with fingers until of fine meal consistency.
Add sugar; blend thoroughly.
Combine milk and water; stir into flour mixture to form medium-soft dough.
Press dough lightly into 10 x 8-inch rectangle on lightly floured surface.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch triangles.
Brush tops with egg; place on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve hot with butter or jam.
Yield: 16.

title: california vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in milk, baking mix, salt, red cayenne pepper and black pepper.
Place zucchini in greased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle with tomatoes and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over cheese mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 to 9 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Put potatoes, onion, pepper, salt, bay leaves, parsley and sausage in stock pot.
Add water till about 2 inches above potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are almost done.
Take sausage out and put to side.
In small bowl mix sour cream, flour and some hot liquid from soup.
Mix till smooth, add to soup pot.
Add sausage back to pot.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: savory turkey gravy
directions: Put drippings in roasting pan; stir in bouillon.
Stir and cook over mild heat, scraping pan.
Remove from heat.
Mix starch and water.
Stir into liquid in pan.
Add poultry seasoning. Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Makes 4 to 5 generous side servings.

title: sweet & sour green beans
directions: In a skillet, fry bacon until crisp. Take out bacon and add sugar and vinegar to drippings. Cook until sugar dissolves. Layer green beans and onion and bacon in a casserole dish. Pour sugar mixture over the layers in the dish. Refrigerate overnight. Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add blueberries or any fruit. Put in large muffin pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Can add chocolate chips, sour cream, pineapple and apple-cinnamon.

title: a good sister recipe
directions: Blend together the ingredients.
Form into one being.
Serve generous portions to everyone you meet daily.

title: hot creamy crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, wine, onion, mustard, garlic and hot pepper sauce in medium sized saucepan.
Fold crabmeat and 1/4 cup parsley in.
Warm over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until hot.
Do not boil.
Spoon into warm chafing dish or serving dish.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley, the almonds and paprika.
Serve with the crackers.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Melt
1 stick butter and mix with 1 pack crumbled Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry orange punch(for 40 people)
directions: For ice ring, put some of the Hawaiian Punch into ring and arrange fruit or strawberries into it and freeze ring one day before serving.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables into bite-size pieces. Combine oil, olive oil, vinegar and remaining ingredients. Stir until well mixed. Pour over vegetables. Cover and chill at least 12 hours. Stir occasionally. Makes 30 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add 1 cup milk to flour mixture. Add 1/2 cup milk to egg yolks; beating well, then add to other mixture.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Cool.
Alternate in layers with bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart onto greased baking sheet.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain and clean salmon.
Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Form into patties and fry
in lightly greased pan.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; when it reaches room temperature add crushed pineapple and sweetened berries, crushed, bananas, nuts and pineapple juice.
Pour half of mixture into clear rectangular dish.
Chill until firm.
Leave other half at room temperature.
When first half is chilled, spread sour cream on top.
Pour remainder of berry mixture over sour cream and chill.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix cheese, milk, butter, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add both flours.
Let rise until doubled.
Put into 2 loaves and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sausage and green beans
directions: Cut sausages into bite-sized pieces and brown in Dutch oven. Remove sausage from pan and set aside.
Remove all but 3 tablespoons of oil from pan.
Add onions and beans.
Saute until onions are clear and yellow.
Add mushrooms, basil, savory, seasoned salt, pepper, potatoes, beef bouillon and sausage.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and place in a large mixing bowl.
With electric mixer, beat in margarine, sugars, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla, cinnamon and eggs; mix well.
Pour into pie crust and bake for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: swiss potato potage
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender. Add flour to make a roux. Add water; stir until smooth. Add potatoes and milk. Simmer until cooked.
Add bouillon, parsley, salt and pepper.
When heated through, stir in grated or shredded cheese until melted. Serve when hot with a crusty French bread.
If using bacon, sprinkle on top of each serving bowl.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Add sour cream; mix in flour, baking powder and salt. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour 1/2 batter into a tube cake pan which has been greased and lightly floured. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon that has been mixed together on top of the batter.
Pour in rest of the batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: munsy's biscuit pudding(old family recipe)
directions: Crumble biscuits.
Remove crusts.
Cover biscuits with just enough warm water to moisten.
Soak several hours or until biscuits dissolve.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add milk and sugar.
Beat until well mixed.
Add flavoring.
Generously grease pudding pan with fresh, unsalted butter.
Pour mix into pan.
Bake slowly until pudding sets.
Do not overbake.

title: ann lander's meat loaf
directions: Beat all ingredients, except tomato sauce and bacon strips, thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with bacon strips (optional).
Pour tomato sauce over the loaf.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Serves six.

title: pinwheels
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with yogurt and rest of ingredients. Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Chill 2 hours and cut into bite size pieces.

title: california hash
directions: Brown ground beef, then add all the other ingredients and serve after cheese has melted.
Serve with Tostado chips or Fritos and a tossed salad.

title: diabetic and low-fat french dressing
directions: Combine tomato soup, salad oil, Sweet 'N Low, vinegar, salt, mustard, ground onion, black pepper and garlic powder.
Mix on low speed for 10 minutes.
May be kept for a long time in refrigerator.

title: summer bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: portuguese fried potatoes
directions: In a heavy 10 to 12-inch skillet, melt the butter in the olive oil over moderate heat.
When the foam begins to subside, add potatoes, turning them frequently.
Cook for 15 minutes until tender and golden brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to heated bowl or platter; sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: pepper glazed cajun chicken
directions: Sprinkle seasoning over chicken.
Heat oil in large pan over medium heat; add chicken and cook 10 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Add onions to drippings in skillet and cook for 2 minutes. Stir in jelly, broth and vinegar.
Return chicken to pan; spoon glaze over chicken.
Cover and cook until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and cook liquid until thick.
Spoon over chicken.

title: made-right pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sour cream and dry pudding mix.
Blend well. Fold in Cool
Whip; pour in pie crust.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: grandmother k-kay's key lime pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: rice jumbo
directions: Mix ingredients together and cover with 1 can mushroom soup to which 1/2 cup milk has been added.
Cover with buttered crumbs. Bake for 1 hour in a 350° moderate oven.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together.
Stir in dry ingredients. Batter will be stiff.
Add chips and M&M's.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Follow directions on the box.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in large heavy kettle.
Drain.
Add all ingredients except cabbage, beans and macaroni.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add more water or broth if needed.

title: crock-pot chicken stew
directions: In crock-pot, combine soup, potatoes, squash, onion, carrots, celery, corn and spices. Put chicken on top, bone side up. Cover with some of the soup. Cook on low 6 to 7 hours until tender. Remove chicken from pot, then remove meat from bones. Set aside.

title: chopped filled bonbon cookies
directions: Cream
Crisco, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix
well.
Press 2 level teaspoonfuls dough around each candy
Kiss,
covering
completely.
Place
pecan half on each. Bake
on ungreased cookie sheet 6 or 7 minutes.
(Cookies don't get
brown.)
Press pecan down into cookies.
Makes 36.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: steak bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Toss meat that has been cut in cubes with flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Put in round casserole and bake uncovered for 20 minutes.
Remove and add all other ingredients; mix well.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
The ingredients make a real flavorful gravy.
Serve over hot noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: pot pie and biscuit dough
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Rub in Crisco a little at a time with a fork.
Add milk slowly and mix to a soft dough.
Roll out on lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thick, for biscuits, thinner for pot pie.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 24 biscuits.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Grease and flour 1 large 9 x 12-inch pan or 2 round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: microwave white rice
directions: Pour ingredients into microwave-safe casserole with lid and cover.
Place in microwave on two sheets of paper towel. Microwave on High for 5 minutes and then microwave on Medium for 15 minutes.
Remove from microwave and use paper towels to clean up any spills.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Pour over flour and nuts.
Mix well and press into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: pastor's favorite
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add orange sherbet and mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: pork chop creole
directions: Brown pork chops; drain grease.
Place an onion slice on each chop; top with a mound of rice.
Pour tomato soup over all.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 1-1/2 qt. casserole dish layer half of the ham, half of the onion and half of the potatoes. Repeat layers. Mix soup, milk and pepper. Pour over potatoes.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Mix pie filling and cinnamon; reserve.
Beat flour, granulated sugar, milk, softened margarine, baking powder, salt and eggs in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently, 2 minutes.
Pour half of the batter (about 2 cups) into pan.
Spoon half of the pie filling mixture (1 cup) over batter in pan; repeat with remaining batter and pie filling mixture.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over pie filling mixture.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar and butter (blender works well for this).
Sift together dry ingredients (flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices).
Add the eggs and vanilla to sugar and butter mixture. Add the dry ingredients alternately with the buttermilk, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Chill dough for several hours or overnight; roll out.
Cut and place on floured cookie sheets. Let stand for 15 minutes.
Fry in deep fat until brown.
Turn twice.
May need a little more flour.

title: easy creamy casserole
directions: *Choose your own ingredients to suit.

title: harvest pumpkin bars
directions: Crumble crackers and mix with coconut, walnuts, and butter. Pat 2/3 of mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9x 2-inch baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon evenly over coconut mixture in pan; sprinkle with remaining coconut mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan, then chill.
Cut into 2 x 3-inch bars.
Yield: about 2 dozen.

title: easy chocolate mousse
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in small bowl; stir and let stand 1 minute.
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Stir together sugar and cocoa; add heavy cream and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until stiff peaks form.
Pour in gelatin mixture and beat until well blended.
Spoon into serving dishes and chill at least 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: caramel pineapple cake
directions: First layer;
mix cake according to directions on box.
Cook in long pan.
When cake is done, poke holes in lay with fork. Second layer; mix pineapple, juice, and cup of sugar in boiler. Boil for one minute.
Then pour over cake layer.
Ice with caramel icing.

title: good dill pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, salt and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
In quart jars put 1 clove garlic, 1 dill head and enough small cucumbers in jar to fill it.
Pour boiling brine over pickles.
Cover each jar with lid and seal.

title: creamy cherry dessert
directions: Mix together. Place in a 9 x 13 pan. Can be frozen or just chilled.

title: punch
directions: Fill with about 2 quarts water.
Add juice of 1 lemon.
Taste.

title: dill dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill 24 hours.
So great.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Mix together beef, pork, rice and egg.
Take cabbage leaves and cook until tender.
Then wrap the meat within the leaves. Brown celery, green pepper and carrots in butter.
Add tomato soup and equal amount of water and cook for 10 minutes.
Cover the meat mixture with tomato mixture.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Watch and add water.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; add eggs, beaten slightly. Sift flour with baking powder (use some of flour mixture with cut up fruit).
Add flour and whiskey; add nuts and coconut.
Stir. Add floured fruits and fold in.
Using Bundt pan, lightly greased and floured, bake in slow oven at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Test with cake tester.
Toothpick should come out clean.

title: peppermint bark
directions: Melt almond bark.
Add crushed peppermint and a drop or two of red food coloring.
Mix all together.
Pour onto a cookie sheet; freeze until hard.
Break into small pieces and put in an airtight container.

title: lipton berry splash
directions: In a large pitcher, combine instant tea powder, sugar, water, cranberry, orange and lemon juices, cinnamon and nutmeg; chill. Garnish, if desired, with orange slices.
Serve with ice.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: crab imperial
directions: In medium pan, melt margarine or butter.
Mix in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly to keep mixture smooth and free from lumps.
Cook until thickened.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread cubes.
Cool.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: hot dip
directions: Combine. Serve with chips.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Beat the persimmon, baking soda, sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add the eggs, flour, sifted spices, nuts and raisins. Drop by spoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: chocanana shake
directions: Cut up the bananas into little slices.
Next, cut the chocolate bar into the little rectangles that are already there. Then pour the milk into the blender.
Add all the bananas and 5 rectangles; blend on low.
Last, put the rest of the Hershey bar in blender.
Blend on medium, then switch to high.

title: potato babka
directions: Beat egg yolks into potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat vigorously until light.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mix.
Spoon potatoes lightly into a buttered baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° or until well puffed.
Serves 4.
